2009年1月20日（星期二），[[贝拉克·奥巴马|贝拉克·奥巴马]]宣誓就任[[美国总统列表|第44任]][[美国总统|美国总统]]。这场就职典礼创下了美国[[首都|首都]][[哥伦比亚特区|哥伦比亚特区]]举办活动出席人数的新纪录，也标志着奥巴马4年总统任期和[[乔·拜登|乔·拜登]]4年[[美国副总统|副总统]]任期的开始。从现场出席人数、以及通过[[电视|电视]]和[[互联网|互联网]]收看转播的观众人数总和来看，这场典礼是世界历史上最受瞩目的事件之一。

2009年是[[亚伯拉罕·林肯|亚伯拉罕·林肯]]诞辰200周年，奥巴马的就职典礼以林肯在[[盖兹堡演说|盖兹堡演说]]中的一句演说词“自由的新生”（{{lang|en|A New Birth of Freedom}}）为主题。奥巴马在讲话中提及林肯所表达的变革、延续与民族团结的理想，并借此在讲话中强调，美国需要以共同牺牲和新的责任感来应对国内外的挑战。

奥巴马等人通过多项活动向林肯表示敬意，首先是在2009年1月17日登上[[费城|费城]]开往哥伦比亚特区的一辆具有纪念意义的火车。整个就职典礼从2009年1月18日开始，21日结束，具体活动包括音乐会、[[马丁·路德·金纪念日|马丁·路德·金纪念日]]的社区服务、宣誓仪式、午宴和游行、就职舞会，以及就职祈祷仪式。1月20日的宣誓就职情况与《[[美国宪法|美国宪法]]》中的规定略有偏差，因此奥巴马于次日重新进行了宣誓。

除出席的社会名流异常之多外，本次[[美国总统就职典礼|总统就职典礼]]中普通民众的参与度也大幅提高，与之前的几次就职典礼对比效果显著。就职典礼国会联合委员会打破传统，首次将[[国家广场|国家广场]]全部向公众开放，让更多的人能够一睹宣誓仪式全貌。许多[[美国公民|美国公民]]获选参加包括火车之旅在内的多项活动，还有慈善者组织面向民众的就职舞会，让通常情况下无法参与就职庆典的[[弱势群体|弱势群体]]也能加入。委员会还首次举办了不收门票或是费用非常低廉的就职舞会，让许多普通市民得以亲身参与盛事。

== 背景 ==
2008年11月4日是美国四年一度的[[选举日_(美国)|总统选举日]]，[[民主党_(美国)|民主党]]候选人[[贝拉克·奥巴马|贝拉克·奥巴马]]在[[2008年美国总统选举|这场选举]]中获胜，成为[[美国总统当选人|总统当选人]]，2009年1月的这场就职典礼也就标识着他任期的开始<ref name='NYT-Nagourney-2008-11-04'>{{cite news | first = Adam | last = Nagourney | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130618092039/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/05/us/politics/05elect.html?_r=0 | title = Obama Wins Election | date = 2008-11-04 | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/05/us/politics/05elect.html?_r=0 | work = The New York Times | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | archivedate = 2013-06-18 | deadurl = no | publisher = The New York Times Company }}</ref>。根据《[[美国宪法|美利坚合众国宪法]]》[[美国宪法第一条|第一条第6款]]，奥巴马于2008年11月16日从[[美国参议院|联邦参议院]]辞职<ref>Letter of resignation from Barack Obama to Richard Cheney, November 18, 2008; published in the ''Congressional Record'', November 19, 2008, page S10609 Communication from the Honorable Barack Obama</ref><ref>{{cite news | title = Obama sets date to leave Senate | archivedate = 2014-01-16 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140116201204/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/us_elections_2008/7728466.stm | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/us_elections_2008/7728466.stm | date = 2008-11-13 | publisher = BBC News | accessdate = 2014-10-25 }}</ref>。2008年12月15日，[[美国选举人团|选举人团]]经投票正式选出奥巴马担任美国总统<ref name='Politico-EC'>{{cite news | first = Andy | last = Barr | title = Electoral College weighs in for Obama | date = 2008-12-15 | url = http://www.politico.com/news/stories/1208/16610.html | work = Politico | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130514092347/http://www.politico.com/news/stories/1208/16610.html | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2013-05-14 }}</ref>。2009年1月8日，[[美国国会|国会]][[两院制|两院]]证实了选举结果<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.pbs.org/newshour/news_summaries/2009/01/summary_08.html | title = News Summary for January 8, 2009 | accessdate = 2014-01-16 | date = 2009-01-08 | publisher = Public Broadcasting Service | work = PBS NewsHour | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140116232524/http://www.pbs.org/newshour/news_summaries/2009/01/summary_08.html | deadurl = yes | archivedate = 2014-01-16 }}</ref>。

奥巴马起初使用的竞选口号是“我们相信变革”（{{lang|en|Change We Can Believe In}}），之后改为“我们需要变革”（{{lang|en|Change We Need}}）<ref>{{cite web | url = http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2008/09/obamas-change-s/ | title = Obama's 'Change' Slogan Gets a Change | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | date = 2008-09-13 | publisher = ABC News Internet Ventures | archivedate = 2014-02-02 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140202145102/http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2008/09/obamas-change-s/ }}</ref>。他是[[美国历史|美国历史]]上首位[[非裔美国人|非裔]]总统，许多人对奥巴马的当选加以庆祝，把他视为前任[[共和党_(美国)|共和党]]总统[[乔治·沃克·布什|乔治·沃克·布什]]之后的改革象征。奥巴马也是第一位在20世纪60年代出生的美国总统，标志着时代性的交替。[[彼得·奥斯泽格|彼得·奥斯泽格]]（{{lang|en|Peter Orszag}}）认为，奥巴马当选后在经济上面临极大挑战，面对着一堆彻底的“经济烂摊子”，[[2007年－2008年环球金融危机|2007至2008年的金融危机]]就是明证<ref>{{cite web | archivedate = 2014-01-16 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140116180358/http://www.upi.com/Top_News/2009/03/08/Orszag-Obama-inherited-economic-woes/UPI-85971236559252/ | title = Orszag: Obama inherited economic woes | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | date = 2009-03-08 | publisher = United Press International | deadurl = no | url = http://www.upi.com/Top_News/2009/03/08/Orszag-Obama-inherited-economic-woes/UPI-85971236559252/ }}</ref>。{{lang|en|[[CNN|CNN]]}}的民意调查显示，与布什相比，奥巴马在这个经济上的绝望时期代表着青春活力和转型，让人们对生活前景更有自信<ref name="kdn">{{cite news | title = History made as Obama sworn in | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140116215942/http://www.nation.co.ke/News/-/1056/517048/-/u1bo54/-/index.html | url = http://www.nation.co.ke/News/-/1056/517048/-/u1bo54/-/index.html | work = Daily Nation | location = Kenya | date = 2009-01-19 | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | archivedate = 2014-01-16 }}</ref>。

== 策划 ==
[[File:ObamaInaugurationCapitolPreparation.jpg|缩略图]]前进行的准备工作]]
就职典礼主要由两个委员会策划，分别是就职典礼国会联合委员会以及2009年总统就职委员会。虽然选举日是2008年11月4日，但国会联合委员会早在2008年9月4日就已经开始了实际建设工作。<ref>{{cite news | title = Construction of 2009 Inaugural Platform Begins with the Ceremonial Driving of the "First Nail" | date = 2008-09-24 | publisher = United States Congress Joint Congressional Committee on Inaugural Ceremonies | archivedate = 2012-10-06 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121006205757/http://inaugural.senate.gov/media/releases/release-09242008-inauguralwebsite.cfm | url = http://inaugural.senate.gov/media/releases/release-09242008-inauguralwebsite.cfm | work = Press Release | accessdate = 2012-10-06 | deadurl = yes }}</ref>

=== 国会联合委员会 ===
总统当选人奥巴马和副总统当选人拜登的宣誓仪式和就职午宴由就职典礼国会联合委员会策划，[[联邦参议员|联邦参议员]][[黛安·范士丹|黛安·范士丹]]担任委员会主席，另外几位成员包括参议员[[罗伯特·班尼特|罗伯特·班尼特]]和[[哈里·瑞德|哈里·瑞德]]以及[[美国众议院|联邦众议员]][[约翰·博纳|约翰·博纳]]、[[斯坦利·霍耶|斯坦利·霍耶]]和[[兰希·佩洛西|兰希·佩洛西]]。[[美国参议院规则和管理委员会|联邦参议院规则和管理委员会]]对国会联合委员会的运作进行监督。<ref>{{cite web | archivedate = 2012-10-06 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121006180456/http://inaugural.senate.gov/cmte/membershiphistory.cfm | deadurl = yes | url = http://inaugural.senate.gov/cmte/membershiphistory.cfm | title = Membership of the Joint Congressional Committee on Inaugural Ceremonies | accessdate = 2012-10-06 | publisher = United States Senate }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140920051231/http://www.inaugural.senate.gov/about/history | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | url = http://www.inaugural.senate.gov/about/history | title = Committee History | publisher = Joint Congressional Committee on Inaugural Ceremonies | archivedate = 2014-09-20 | deadurl = yes }}</ref>

就职典礼主题“自由的新生”由国会联合委员会确定<ref name="JCCIC-Inaugural Theme-2008-11-05">{{cite news | title = Senator Feinstein Announces 2009 Inaugural Theme | date = 2008-11-05 | publisher = United States Congress Joint Congressional Committee on Inaugural Ceremonies | work = Press Release | accessdate = 2009-01-15 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121007031936/http://inaugural.senate.gov/media/releases/release-11052008-inauguralwebsite.cfm | url = http://inaugural.senate.gov/media/releases/release-11052008-inauguralwebsite.cfm | archivedate = 2012-10-07 | deadurl = yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://nypost.com/2009/01/13/o-to-arrive-in-a-lincoln/ | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140118070753/http://nypost.com/2009/01/13/o-to-arrive-in-a-lincoln/ | title = Obama's inaugural theme echoes Lincoln | last = Lisi | first = Clemente | date = 2008-11-06 | work = The Washington Times | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | archivedate = 2014-01-18 }}</ref>，这句话源于[[南北战争|南北战争]]时期前总统[[亚伯拉罕·林肯|亚伯拉罕·林肯]]在[[盖兹堡演说|盖兹堡演说]]中的一句话<ref name="JCCIC-Inaugural Theme-2008-11-05" /><ref>{{cite book | author = Boritt, Gabor | year = 2006 | title = The Gettysburg Gospel: The Lincoln Speech That Nobody Knows | url = https://archive.org/details/gettysburggospel00bori | publisher = Simon & Schuster | page = 432 | isbn = 0-7432-8820-3}}</ref>。委员会选择这一主题来向林肯诞辰200周年致敬，表达出“林肯希望那些为保护美国献出生命的人能够带领国家走向‘自由的新生’的理想”<ref>{{cite news | url = http://inaugural.senate.gov/history/chronology/bhobama2009/theme.cfm | title = 'A New Birth of Freedom'—2009 Inaugural Theme | year = 2008 | publisher = United States Congress Joint Congressional Committee on Inaugural Ceremonies | accessdate = 2012-10-06 | archivedate = 2012-10-06 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121006181851/http://inaugural.senate.gov/history/chronology/bhobama2009/theme.cfm | deadurl = yes }}</ref>。对此奥巴马表示，希望这一主题能够“给予美国人信心，今天的祖国会像林肯的时代那样，找到度过任何危机的办法”<ref>{{cite news | title = Barack Obama's Inauguration Is One for the History Books | last = Walsh | first = Kenneth, T. | date = 2009-01-20 | work = U.S. News & World Report | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | archivedate = 2014-02-02 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140202102808/http://www.usnews.com/news/obama/articles/2009/01/20/barack-obamas-inauguration-is-one-for-the-history-books | deadurl = no | url = http://www.usnews.com/news/obama/articles/2009/01/20/barack-obamas-inauguration-is-one-for-the-history-books }}</ref>。

国会联合委员会于2008年12月17日发布次年1月20日就职典礼活动的全部日程，虽然奥巴马之前曾特别说明，自己会在宣誓仪式上使用包括中间名“侯赛因”（{{lang|en|Hussein}}）在内的全名，但日程中仍是以“贝拉克·{{lang|en|H}}·奥巴马”来称呼总统当选人<ref name="ItRNBfUD">{{cite news | archivedate = 2013-12-16 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131216211640/http://www.foxnews.com/story/2008/12/16/obama-to-resurrect-middle-name-for-inauguration-day/ | url = http://www.foxnews.com/story/2008/12/16/obama-to-resurrect-middle-name-for-inauguration-day/ | title = Obama to Resurrect Middle Name for Inauguration Day | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | date = 2008-12-16 | publisher = Fox News | deadurl = yes }}</ref>。奥巴马决定“遵循传统”使用全名“贝拉克·侯赛因·奥巴马”，不会在就职典礼上采用别的名字发表声明<ref name="IBHODSS">{{cite news | publisher = The Washington Post Company | url = http://voices.washingtonpost.com/sleuth/2008/12/president-elect_obama_has_said.html | title = I Barack Hussein Obama Do Solemnly Swear... | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | date = 2008-12-18 | work = The Washington Post | author = Akers, Mary Beth | archive-date = 2012-03-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120323152610/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/sleuth/2008/12/president-elect_obama_has_said.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。[[奥巴马2008年美国总统竞选活动|竞选期间]]，奥巴马的反对者曾试图利用他的中间名来暗示候选人是[[穆斯林|穆斯林]]<ref name="IBHODSS" />。

[[哥伦比亚特区议会|哥伦比亚特区议会]]通过立法，允许酒吧和餐馆在就职典礼活动期间为参与活动的人士提供不间断接待服务<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=98280231 | title = Inauguration: Expect Nonstop Drink, Crowds | last = Keyes | first = Allison | date = 2008-12-21 | publisher = National Public Radio | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140116200418/http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=98280231 | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | archivedate = 2014-01-16 }}</ref>。哥伦比亚特区[[市长|市长]][[阿德里安·芬蒂|阿德里安·芬蒂]]（{{lang|en|Adrian Fenty}}）在同国会联合委员会达成一致后签署法案，允许酒吧和餐馆在典礼日期前一个周末期间保持24小时营业，但每天供应含[[酒精|酒精]]饮料的时间只能到[[北美东部时区|东部时间]]凌晨4点为止<ref name="SCEBHfIaBI">{{cite web | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090211183825/http://www.salon.com/politics/war_room/2008/12/17/dc_bars/ | deadurl = yes | url = http://www.salon.com/politics/war_room/2008/12/17/dc_bars/ | title = D.C. bars won't stay open quite so late for inauguration | accessdate = 2009-02-11 | date = 2008-12-17 | work = Salon | publisher = Salon Media Group, Inc. | archivedate = 2009-02-11 | author = Alex Koppelman }}</ref><ref name="JCCIC-alcohol">{{cite web | title = Senators Feinstein and Bennett Urge DC Government To Reverse Emergency Alcohol Law | publisher = United States Congress Joint Congressional Committee on Inaugural Ceremonies | date = 2008-12-09 | archivedate = 2012-10-07 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121007032044/http://inaugural.senate.gov/media/releases/release-12102008-fentygray.cfm | url = http://inaugural.senate.gov/media/releases/release-12102008-fentygray.cfm | accessdate = 2012-10-07 }}</ref>。华盛顿都会区饭店协会同意支付1月19日由[[华盛顿都会区运输管理局|华盛顿都会区运输管理局]]提供的加开列车服务，以便满足前来参加典礼活动的人员运输需要，并提供足够的工作人员<ref>{{cite news | publisher = The Washington Post Company | url = http://voices.washingtonpost.com/inauguration-watch/2009/01/metro_extends_service_on_inaug.html | title = Metro Extends Service on Inaugural Eve Until 2 am | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | date = 2009-01-13 | work = The Washington Post | author = Nakamura, David A | archive-date = 2011-12-24 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20111224023312/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/inauguration-watch/2009/01/metro_extends_service_on_inaug.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

=== 总统就职委员会 ===
2009年总统就职委员会组织了多场与总统当选人和副总统当选人就职有关的活动，如搭乘火车、音乐会、游行、舞会和祈祷仪式等，[[威廉·M·戴利|威廉·戴利]]、[[潘妮·普利茨克|潘妮·普利茨克]]、[[小约翰·罗杰斯|约翰·罗杰斯]]、帕特里克·瑞安（{{lang|en|Patrick Ryan}}）和[[朱莉安娜·斯穆特|朱莉安娜·斯穆特]]（{{lang|en|Julianna Smoot}}）共同担任委员会主席。<ref>{{cite news |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116183005/http://blogs.suntimes.com/sweet/2008/11/obama_presidential_inauguratio.html |url=http://blogs.suntimes.com/sweet/2008/11/obama_presidential_inauguratio.html |title=Obama Presidential Inauguration Committee announced. Daley, Pritzker, Rogers, Smoot and Ryan co-chair. |accessdate=2014-10-25 |date=2008-12-25 |work=Chicago Sun-Times |author=Sweet, Lynn |archivedate=2014-01-16 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

总统就职委员会将从[[美国国会大厦|美国国会大厦]]一直延伸到[[林肯纪念堂|林肯纪念堂]]的整个[[国家广场|国家广场]]全部向公众开放，让尽可能多的人得以目睹宣誓仪式，这在历史上尚属首次<ref name="foxmall">{{cite news |archivedate=2011-09-29 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110929043744/http://origin.foxnews.com/wires/2008Dec04/0%2C4670%2CInaugurationMall%2C00.html |url=http://origin.foxnews.com/wires/2008Dec04/0,4670,InaugurationMall,00.html |title=National Mall will be open for Obama inauguration |last=Zongker |first=Brett |date=2008-12-04 |publisher=Fox News |accessdate=2011-09-29 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。委员会为持有就职典礼保留门票的人士空出了广场靠国会大厦的一片区域<ref name="foxmall" /><ref name="AVGttPIoBO">{{cite web | archivedate = 2014-09-24 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140924053730/http://www.usnews.com/news/obama/articles/2008/12/17/a-visitors-guide-to-the-presidential-inauguration-of-barack-obama | title = A Visitor's Guide to the Presidential Inauguration of Barack Obama | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | date = 2008-12-17 | work = U.S. News & World Report | author = Ruggeri, Amanda | url = http://www.usnews.com/news/obama/articles/2008/12/17/a-visitors-guide-to-the-presidential-inauguration-of-barack-obama }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/20/AR2009012004497.html | title = A historic inauguration draws throngs to the Mall. | author = Shear, Michael D. and Kornblut, Anne E. | date = 2009-01-21 | work = The Washington Post | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | publisher = The Washington Post Company | archive-date = 2020-05-17 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200517224548/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/20/AR2009012004497.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。委员会希望，开放整个国家广场能够让这成为历史上最开放，最便于公众观看的总统就职典礼活动，让那些无法取得宣誓仪式门票的人能够亲身体验盛事<ref name="foxmall" />。为了便于人们观看典礼，并且能够听到声音，委员会在广场各处都安放了[[超大屏幕|超大屏幕]]<ref name="mall">{{cite news |accessdate=2014-10-25 |first=Matthew |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116182322/http://washingtonindependent.com/20933/national-mall-will-open-to-public-for-inauguration |url=http://washingtonindependent.com/20933/national-mall-will-open-to-public-for-inauguration |title=National Mall Will Open to Public for Inauguration |last=DeLong |date=2008-12-04 |work=The Washington Independent |archivedate=2014-01-16 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。

虽然有批评称这样的大型活动不可能实现[[碳足印|低碳]]，但总统就职委员会还是在活动规划过程中采取了[[零浪费|环保]]措施。平台地毯可供循环使用，活动结束后还会把室外可回收的物品取回<ref name="green">{{cite web | last = Yager | first = Jordy | title = Green carpet won't quite cover Inaugural footprint | work = The Hill | date = 2009-01-13 | url = http://thehill.com/leading-the-news/green-carpet-wont-quite-cover-inaugural-footprint-2009-01-13.html | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090225230246/http://thehill.com/leading-the-news/green-carpet-wont-quite-cover-inaugural-footprint-2009-01-13.html | accessdate = 2009-02-25 | archivedate = 2009-02-25 | deadurl = yes }}</ref>，请柬和就职舞会门票也是采用再生纸制作<ref name="green2">{{cite web | last = Miller | first = Sunlen | title = Obama Team Aims to Go Green This Inaugural | publisher = ABC News | date = 2009-01-14 | url = http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2009/01/obama-team-aims/ | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131221104702/http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2009/01/obama-team-aims/ | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | archivedate = 2013-12-21 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。

