2009年美国总统就职委员会希望能够筹集到与2005年乔治·沃克·布什第二次就职典礼时相比更多的个人小额捐款。2009年的捐款额度限制为每人不超过5万美元，而2005年时针对个人或企业的限额则有25万美元<ref name="OistbtmeiUh" />。截至2009年1月30日，总统就职委员会已经筹得了超过5300万美元，其中有至少458人的捐款额达到委员会划定的5万美元最高值<ref name="fundstotal">{{cite news | archivedate = 2014-01-16 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140116213257/http://www.boston.com/news/nation/articles/2009/01/30/inaugural_fund_raising_exceeds_53m/ | url = http://www.boston.com/news/nation/articles/2009/01/30/inaugural_fund_raising_exceeds_53m/ | title = Inaugural fund-raising exceeds $53m | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | date = 2009-01-30 | work = The Boston Globe | author = Mooney, Brian C. | deadurl = no }}</ref>，其中包括[[乔治·索罗斯|乔治·索罗斯]]、[[哈莉·贝瑞|哈莉·贝瑞]]、[[杰米·福克斯|杰米·福克斯]]和[[乔治·卢卡斯|乔治·卢卡斯]]等名流<ref name="Or$mfi">{{cite news | title = Hollywood Coughs Up Cash for Obama Inaugural | url = http://voices.washingtonpost.com/sleuth/2008/12/despite_concerns_about_donor_f.html | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | date = 2008-12-15 | work = The Washington Post | author = Akers, Mary Ann | archive-date = 2010-10-31 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101031215939/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/sleuth/2008/12/despite_concerns_about_donor_f.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。与往年一样，委员会对竞选捐款设立了严格的规定，企业、[[政治行动委员会|政治行动委员会]]、已经登记的联邦[[游说集团|游说分子]]、[[工会|工商联盟]]、已经登记的外国机构和非美国公民的捐献都受到严格限制<ref name="fundstotal" /><ref>{{cite news | archivedate = 2014-10-25 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141025150704/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/26/us/politics/26inaug.html?_r=0 | deadurl = no | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/26/us/politics/26inaug.html?_r=0 | title = Obama Places Stringent Limits on Inaugural Contributions | last = Seelye | first = Katherine Q. | date = 2008-12-25 | work = The New York Times | accessdate = 2014-10-25 }}</ref>。不过，委员会还是接受了一些虽然没有登记成联邦游说集团，但的确有在联邦政府积极进行游说活动的人士捐赠，如{{lang|en|[[Google|Google]]}}[[董事长|执行主席]][[埃里克·施密特|埃里克·施密特]]和[[微软|微软]][[首席执行官|首席执行官]][[史蒂夫·巴尔默|史蒂夫·巴尔默]]<ref name="Or$mfi" />。

根据筹款的效果，以及对参加就职典礼人数的估算，总统就职委员会将就职典礼的预算定在1.6至1.7亿美元，其中庆祝活动占了约4500万美元<ref name="fundstotal" />。[[美国联邦政府|联邦政府]]捐出约4900万美元，其中120万美元用于支付实际宣誓仪式的成本<ref name="OistbtmeiUh">{{cite news | archivedate = 2014-05-17 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140517223846/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/jan/14/barack-obama-inauguration-cost | url = http://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/jan/14/barack-obama-inauguration-cost | title = Obama's inauguration set to be the most expensive in US history: The $150m (￡102m) cost of the celebration will dwarf the amount spent on George Bush's inauguration in 2005 | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | date = 2009-01-14 | work = The Guardian | location = United Kingdom | author = MacAskill, Ewen | deadurl = no }}</ref><ref name="fundstotal" /><ref name="abc">{{cite news | first = Scott | last = Mayerowitz | title = What Recession? The $170 million Inauguration | date = 2009-01-19 | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140908151015/http://abcnews.go.com/Business/Inauguration/story?id=6665946&page=1 | url = http://abcnews.go.com/Business/Inauguration/story?id=6665946&page=1 | publisher = ABC News | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2014-09-08 }}</ref>。哥伦比亚特区以及邻近的[[马里兰州|马里兰州]]和[[弗吉尼亚州|弗吉尼亚州]]预计，为了满足就职典礼活动的相应需要，单警察、消防和医疗服务方面就需要花费超过7500万美元<ref name="OistbtmeiUh" /><ref name="abc" />。为了帮助筹集资金，总统乔治·沃克·布什宣布联邦地区进入[[紧急状态|紧急状态]]，以便在有必要时从[[联邦紧急事务管理局|联邦紧急事务管理局]]获取资金<ref>{{cite news | title = Bush Declares State of Emergency for Inauguration | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141025152142/http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/01/13/bush-declares-state-of-emergency-for-inauguration/?_php=true&_type=blogs&_r=0 | date = 2009-01-13 | work = The New York Times | author = Stolberg, Sheryl Gay | publisher = The New York Times Company | archivedate = 2014-10-25 | deadurl = no | url = http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/01/13/bush-declares-state-of-emergency-for-inauguration/?_php=true&_type=blogs&_r=0 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title = Inauguration Watch: A State of Emergency? | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | date = 2009-01-13 | work = Wall Street Journal | author = McKinnon, John D. | archivedate = 2014-01-16 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140116191353/http://blogs.wsj.com/washwire/2009/01/13/inauguration-watch-a-state-of-emergency/ | url = http://blogs.wsj.com/washwire/2009/01/13/inauguration-watch-a-state-of-emergency/ }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://voices.washingtonpost.com/inauguration-watch/2009/01/bush_declares_state_of_emergen.html | title = Bush Declares State of Emergency for Inauguration | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | date = 2009-01-13 | work = The Washington Post | author = Nakamura, David A. | publisher = The Washington Post Company | archive-date = 2012-10-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121005174739/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/inauguration-watch/2009/01/bush_declares_state_of_emergen.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

=== 请柬和门票 ===
国会大厦楼层及其附近保留位置的请柬和彩色编码门票由总统就职委员会和第111届联邦国会议员向相应[[重要人物|贵宾]]及普通市民发放，这些位置可以近距离观看宣誓仪式<ref>{{cite news | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130619182038/http://www.mgwashington.com/index.php/news/article/obamas-inauguration-will-be-tough-ticket/2119/ | title = Obama's inauguration will be tough ticket | last = Dominello | archivedate = 2013-06-19 | url = http://www.mgwashington.com/index.php/news/article/obamas-inauguration-will-be-tough-ticket/2119/ | first = Amy | date = 2008-11-10 | publisher = Media General News Service | accessdate = 2013-06-19 }}</ref>。世界各地驻美国大使、正在美国的外交使团首脑及其配偶都收到了请柬和门票，但其他外国代表人士不在获邀之列；美国的许多政治家以及各个行业名流都获得了邀请。[[美国众议院|联邦众议员]]和[[美国参议院|参议员]]向公众发放就职典礼的免费门票，但由于申请人数远远超过容纳能力，门票只能通过抽签或是先到先得的方式赠送。<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/Congress-to-Distribute-Inaugural-Tickets-Starting-Monday.html | title = Congress to receive inaugural tickets today | date = 2009-01-13 | publisher = WRC-TV (Washington, D.C.) | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140709062459/http://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/Congress-to-Distribute-Inaugural-Tickets-Starting-Monday.html | archivedate = 2014-07-09 | deadurl = yes | accessdate = 2014-10-25 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2009/01/12/tickets-obama-inauguration-create-stir-capitol-hill/ | title = Tickets to Obama inauguration create stir on Capitol Hill | author = Pergram, C. | date = 2009-01-12 | publisher = Fox News | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121021184311/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2009/01/12/tickets-obama-inauguration-create-stir-capitol-hill/ | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | archivedate = 2012-10-21 | deadurl = yes }}</ref>

由于保留位置的门票数量有限，但需求量又非常高，因此一些人将所获得的门票通过票贩子、网上拍卖或分类广告出售<ref>{{cite news | title = Senate votes to ban inauguration ticket scalping | date = 2009-01-14 | publisher = Reuters | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | first = Ross | last = Colvin | archivedate = 2013-07-04 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130704213657/http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/01/15/us-usa-obama-inauguration-tickets-idUSTRE50D7O220090115 | url = http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/01/15/us-usa-obama-inauguration-tickets-idUSTRE50D7O220090115 }}</ref>。位于国会大厦倒影池后方的站立空间保留位置门票最高炒到了每张1750美元，位于倒影池前方的站立空间保留位置则炒至每张5500美元，国会大厦地层的贵宾位置更高达每张2万美元<ref name="tixscalping">{{cite news | url = http://voices.washingtonpost.com/washingtonpostinvestigations/2009/01/inaugural_tickets_still_sellin.html | title = $20K Inaugural Tickets for Sale as Congress Debates Ban | last = Kravitz | first = Derek | date = 2009-01-14 | work = The Washington Post | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | publisher = The Washington Post Company | archive-date = 2011-09-17 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110917170406/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/washingtonpostinvestigations/2009/01/inaugural_tickets_still_sellin.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。根据报道，[[德克萨斯州|德克萨斯州]]联邦众议员[[泰德·坡|泰德·坡]]（{{lang|en|Ted Poe}}）的一位前任立法助理试图通过{{lang|en|[[Craigslist|Craigslist]]}}[[分类广告|分类广告]]网站和[[电子邮件|电子邮件]]把5张门票以4500美元的价格卖给一位买家，但遭对方曝光<ref name="autogenerated2">{{cite news | url = http://voices.washingtonpost.com/sleuth/2009/01/selling_inauguration_tickets_i.html | title = Senate Cracks Down on Inaugural Scalping After GOP Aide Nabbed | last = Akers | first = Mary Ann | date = 2009-01-13 | work = The Washington Post | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | publisher = The Washington Post Company | archive-date = 2012-10-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121005174752/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/sleuth/2009/01/selling_inauguration_tickets_i.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

宣誓仪式门票的[[黄牛_(中介人)|倒卖]]以及相应引发的欺诈犯罪活动引起了联邦和州政府的注意<ref name="latimes">{{cite news | url = http://www.latimes.com/business/la-fi-obamatix14-2008nov14-story.html | title = EBay removes offers of Obama inauguration tickets | date = 2008-11-14 | work = Los Angeles Times | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141020013824/http://www.latimes.com/business/la-fi-obamatix14-2008nov14-story.html | accessdate = 2014-10-25 | first = David | last = Colker | archivedate = 2014-10-20 }}</ref>。就职典礼国会联合委员会主席、联邦参议员黛安·范士丹于2008年11月中旬提出法案，对销售宣誓仪式门票的行为发出禁令<ref>{{cite news | url = http://lostintransition.nationaljournal.com/2008/11/ban-on-scalping-inaugural-tickets-stalls.php | title = Ban on Scalping Inaugural Tickets Stalls in Senate | last = Harder | first = Amy | date = 2008-11-21 | work = National Journal | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120317230712/http://lostintransition.nationaljournal.com/2008/11/ban-on-scalping-inaugural-tickets-stalls.php | accessdate = 2012-03-17 | archivedate = 2012-03-17 | deadurl = yes }}</ref>。同时国会联合委员会还与在线拍卖运营商、门票转售和分类广告服务提供商取得联系，禁止这些门票继续销售。为此，{{lang|en|[[StubHub|StubHub]]}}和{{lang|en|[[EBay|EBay]]}}都同意在其拥有的所有站点上禁止宣誓仪式门票销售行为<ref name="tixscalping" /><ref name="latimes" /><ref>{{cite news | title = Feinstein lauds eBay for ticket ban | last = Yager | first = Jordy | date = 2008-11-13 | work = The Hill}}</ref>。由于部分门票是由总统就职委员会为筹款而发行，因此范士丹在2008年12月对法案加以修正，不对这一部分门票销售设限后重新提出禁止宣誓仪式门票销售的法案<ref>{{cite news | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120303204106/http://lostintransition.nationaljournal.com/mt/mt-search.cgi?tag=Legislation&blog_id=49&IncludeBlogs=49 | title = Feinstein Releases Text of Scalping Bill | last = Harder | first = Amy | date = 2009-01-07 | work = National Journal | accessdate = 2012-03-03 | archivedate = 2012-03-03 | deadurl = yes | url = http://lostintransition.nationaljournal.com/mt/mt-search.cgi?tag=Legislation&blog_id=49&IncludeBlogs=49 }}</ref>。不过，联邦参议院未能及时通过最终的法案，导致法案在最后几天的[[跛腳鴨|跛腳鴨]]立法会议期间胎死腹中<ref>{{cite news | url = http://lostintransition.nationaljournal.com/2008/12/inaugural-scalping-ban-dies-in-senate.php | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120606234256/http://lostintransition.nationaljournal.com/2008/12/inaugural-scalping-ban-dies-in-senate.php | title = Ban on Scalping Inaugural Tickets Dies in Senate | last = Harder | first = Amy | date = 2008-12-15 | work = National Journal | accessdate = 2012-06-06 | archivedate = 2012-06-06 }}</ref>。

== 就职典礼前的活动 ==
=== 火车之旅：纪念林肯 ===
2007年1月17日，为纪念亚伯拉罕·林肯诞辰200周年，奥巴马登上火车，重现1861年林肯从[[宾夕法尼亚州|宾夕法尼亚州]][[费城|费城]]前往哥伦比亚特区的最后一段火车之旅<ref name="USAToday-Jackson-2008-12-19">{{cite news | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121103023929/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/politics/2008-12-15-obamatrain_N.htm?csp=34 | url = http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/politics/2008-12-15-obamatrain_N.htm?csp=34 | title = Obama's inaugural train to start in Philly | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2008-12-15 | work = USA Today | last = Jackson | first = David | archivedate = 2012-11-03 | deadurl = no }}</ref><ref name="OAiWATT">{{cite news | first = Jeff | last = Zeleny | title = Obama arrives in Washington after train trip | publisher = The New York Times Company | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/18/us/politics/18obama.html?adxnnl=1&ref=politics&adxnnlx=1414257278-0toYiUiy3DpirCLpIyASZA | work = The New York Times | date = 2009-01-17 | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | archivedate = 2014-10-25 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141025171616/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/18/us/politics/18obama.html?adxnnl=1&ref=politics&adxnnlx=1414257278-0toYiUiy3DpirCLpIyASZA }}</ref>，当年林肯是乘火车从[[伊利诺伊州|伊利诺伊州]][[斯普林菲尔德_(伊利诺伊州)|斯普林菲尔德]]出发，前往首都参加自己的就职典礼<ref name="OtrtDiattL">{{cite news | archivedate = 2013-06-19 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130619073933/http://www.freep.com/article/20090117/OBAMAINAUGURATION10/90117036 | url = http://www.freep.com/article/20090117/OBAMAINAUGURATION10/90117036 | title = Obama train rolls into D.C.; now the pomp, pagentry, parties begin | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2009-01-17 | work = Detroit Free Press | author = Gray, Kathleen }}</ref><ref name="OtcIlyb">{{cite news| title = Obama to crowds: 'I love you back'| url = http://www.cnn.com/2009/POLITICS/01/17/obama.train/| publisher = Cable News Network| date = 2009-02-08| accessdate = 2009-01-17| archive-date = 2009-01-21| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090121105852/http://www.cnn.com/2009/POLITICS/01/17/obama.train/| dead-url = no}}</ref>。奥巴马乘坐的火车车厢是乔治亚300型（{{lang|en|Georgia 300}}），2008年[[民主党_(美国)|民主党]]总统[[初选|初选]]竞选期间，他也是乘坐同一节老式车厢在宾夕法尼亚州巡回宣传<ref name="prestour">{{cite news |url=http://blogs.suntimes.com/sweet/2009/01/aboard_the_obama_express.html |title=Aboard the Obama express |last=Sweet |first=Lynn |date=2009-01-17 |work=Chicago Sun Times |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707012213/http://blogs.suntimes.com/sweet/2009/01/aboard_the_obama_express.html |accessdate=2014-10-26 |archivedate=2014-07-07 }}</ref>。奥巴马的夫人[[米歇尔·奥巴马|米歇尔]]，两人的女儿玛丽亚（{{lang|en|Malia}}）和萨莎（{{lang|en|Sasha}}）以及许多朋友和嘉宾在这段火车之旅中陪同总统当选人<ref name="prestour" />。
[[File:Obama_train_ride.jpg|缩略图]]

奥巴马邀请了41位自己在总统竞选期间认识的“美国普通人”登上火车，陪同自己前往哥伦比亚特区并出席包括宣誓仪式、游行和就职舞会在内的多项其它就职典礼活动<ref name="OtrtDiattL" /><ref name="OTTRTH">{{cite news | url = http://www.cbsnews.com/news/obama-takes-train-ride-to-history/ | title = Obama Takes Train Ride To History: President-Elect Retraces Lincoln's Route From Philadelphia To Washington; Next Stop: Inauguration | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2009-01-17 | publisher = CBS Interactive Inc. | work = CBSNews.com | archivedate = 2014-10-25 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141025171803/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/obama-takes-train-ride-to-history/ }}</ref><ref name="citizens">{{cite news | title = Obama invites 'Everyday Americans' to join Whistle Stop Tour to DC for inaugural festivities | date = 2009-01-07 | work = NBCNews.com | agency = Associated Press | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141025172033/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/28538921/ns/politics-inauguration/t/everyday-americans-invited-whistle-stop/ | archivedate = 2014-10-25 | deadurl = no | url = http://www.nbcnews.com/id/28538921/ns/politics-inauguration/t/everyday-americans-invited-whistle-stop/ }}</ref>。这些普通市民包括马特·孔茨（{{lang|en|Matt Kuntz}}）和[[莉莉·莱德贝特|莉莉·莱德贝特]]（{{lang|en|Lilly Ledbetter}}），他们都曾在总统竞选期间向总统分享过自己的故事<ref name="citizens" /><ref>{{cite web | archivedate = 2012-10-19 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121019091229/http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/Inauguration/story?id=6669384&page=1 | url = http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/Inauguration/story?id=6669384&page=1 | title = Obama Express Pulls into Home Station: 'You're Never Too Old to Toot the Horn,' President-Elect Jokes | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2009-01-17 | publisher = ABC News | author = Khan, Huma, Sunlen Miller and Jake Tapper | deadurl = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.cbsnews.com/news/an-everyday-american-on-obamas-train/ | title = An "Everyday" American on Obama's Train: CBS Evening News: Dover Teacher And Anti-Domestic Violence Advocate Among Passengers On Historic Trip | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141026020537/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/an-everyday-american-on-obamas-train/ | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2009-01-17 | publisher = CBS News | author = David, Priya | archivedate = 2014-10-26 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title = Obama's connections, from campaign trail to inaugural train | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2009-01-16 | work = USA Today | author = Keily, Kathy | archivedate = 2012-11-03 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121103023934/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/washington/2009-01-15-obamasupporters_N.htm | url = http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/washington/2009-01-15-obamasupporters_N.htm | deadurl = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.gadsdentimes.com/article/20090108/NEWS/901070283 | title = Ledbetter to ride on Obama's train tour | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2009-01-08 | work = Gadsden Times | location = Gadsden, AL | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120624023035/http://www.gadsdentimes.com/article/20090108/NEWS/901070283 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2012-06-24 }}</ref>。孔茨的兄弟曾参加[[海湾战争|海湾战争]]，但回到家园后因[[创伤后心理压力紧张症候群|创伤后心理压力紧张症候群]][[自杀|自杀]]身亡，从此孔茨开始致力于改善[[伊拉克战争|伊拉克战争]]退伍军人的精神健康检查待遇<ref name="citizens" />。莱德贝特得知自己曾在多年前因[[性别|性别]]方面原因在薪酬待遇上遭到雇主的歧视待遇，但由于未能在歧视行为发生的180天诉讼有效期限内提出起诉，[[美国最高法院|联邦最高法院]]没有支持她的诉讼请求<ref name="citizens" />。奥巴马在就任总统9天后签署了《[[2009年莉莉·莱德贝特公平薪酬法|莉莉·莱德贝特公平薪酬法]]》，把因薪酬歧视导致的雇员向雇主索赔期限从最初一次歧视行为后180天扩展到任何一次歧视行为后180天<ref>{{cite news | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121017064740/http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2009/jan/29/obama-signs-ledbetter-fair-pay-act/ | url = http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2009/jan/29/obama-signs-ledbetter-fair-pay-act/ | title = Obama signs Ledbetter fair-pay act | last = Bellantoni | first = Christina | date = 2009-01-29 | work = The Washington Times | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | archivedate = 2012-10-17 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。

奥巴马与数百名支持者在费城[[30街车站|30街车站]]举行市政厅会面并拉开这次火车之旅的序幕<ref name="OAiWATT" /><ref name="OtcIlyb" />。列车的第一站是[[特拉华州|特拉华州]]的[[威尔明顿_(特拉华州)|威尔明顿]]，副总统当选人拜登及其家人登上了火车。拜登曾因每天乘[[美铁|美铁]]从威尔明顿到哥伦比亚特区上班而得到了一个叫“美铁乔”（{{lang|en|Amtrak Joe}}）的绰号，他一直支持为美国通勤[[铁路运输|铁路运输]]增加经费<ref>{{cite news | publisher = The New York Times Company | url = http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/09/16/riding-the-rails-with-amtrak-joe/?_php=true&_type=blogs&_r=0 | title = Riding the Rails With Amtrak Joe | last = Leibovich | first = Mark | work = The New York Times | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141026024212/http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/09/16/riding-the-rails-with-amtrak-joe/?_php=true&_type=blogs&_r=0 | archivedate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2008-09-16 | accessdate = 2014-10-26 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | publisher = The New York Times Company | archivedate = 2014-10-26 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141026024344/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/23/fashion/23biden.html | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/23/fashion/23biden.html?gwh=704AFC9EE37D033D72C42D494A566EE6&gwt=pay | title = 'Amtrak Joe' No More | last = Bosman | first = Julie | date = 2008-11-21 | work = The New York Times | accessdate = 2014-10-26 }}</ref>。火车继续前进，奥巴马在第二站[[巴尔的摩|巴尔的摩]]向约4万人发表演说<ref name="OAiWATT" />。

奥巴马在向群众演说时强调主题“自由的新生”，还使用了包括“更好的天使”（{{lang|en|better angels}}）、“新独立宣言”（{{lang|en|a new declaration of independence}}）之类与林肯有关的词句<ref name="OAiWATT" />。他提醒众人：“我们永远都不能忘记，自己是第一批[[爱国者_(美国革命)|爱国者]]的继承人，他们都是普普通通的男女老少，在一切都显得没有希望时仍然拒绝放弃，并且不知何故仍然相信他们能够让这个世界焕然一新”<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.examiner.com/article/obama-s-whistle-stop-train-tour-philadelphia-speech | title = Obama's Whistle-Stop Train Tour - Philadelphia speech | date = 2009-01-17 | work = Examiner.com | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141026025511/http://www.examiner.com/article/obama-s-whistle-stop-train-tour-philadelphia-speech | archivedate = 2014-10-26 | publisher = AXS Digital Group LLC | 10 =  }}</ref>。成千上万的好心人聚集在火车沿途各处，向经过的列车欢呼、拍照，并且挥舞着[[美国国旗|美国国旗]]和自制的标语<ref name="OAiWATT" />，奥巴马则向热情的群众报以呼喊“我也爱你们”<ref name="OtcIlyb" /><ref>{{cite news | work = The New York Times | author = Powell, Michael | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/22/us/politics/22obama.html?gwh=774B81FC1E2F1C1C4C874E6808992B0A&gwt=pay | title = After a Year on the Road, Obama Is Changing His Tempo | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2008-10-21 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141026025925/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/22/us/politics/22obama.html?gwh=774B81FC1E2F1C1C4C874E6808992B0A&gwt=pay | archivedate = 2014-10-26 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。火车之旅时长一天，最终在哥伦比亚特区的[[联合车站_(华盛顿特区)|联合车站]]结束<ref name="OtrtDiattL" />。

=== 我们是一家音乐会 ===
[[File:20090118_We_Are_One.jpg|缩略图]]举办“我们是一家”音乐会，奥巴马夫妇在此向观众挥手致意。]]
2009年1月18日，奥巴马到达哥伦比亚特区次日，[[林肯纪念堂|林肯纪念堂]]举办了一场名为“我们是一家”的就职音乐会，有超过36位名流在音乐会上表演节目或是朗读历史性语段<ref name="WAOTOIC">{{cite news | url = http://variety.com/2009/scene/reviews/we-are-one-the-obama-inaugural-celebration-1200473270/ | title = We Are One: The Obama Inaugural Celebration | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2009-01-18 | work = Variety | author = Gallo, Phil | publisher = Variety Media, LLC | archive-date = 2019-06-22 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190622015648/https://variety.com/2009/scene/reviews/we-are-one-the-obama-inaugural-celebration-1200473270/ | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="JBAFasaOip">{{cite news | archivedate = 2014-07-31 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140731125946/http://articles.latimes.com/2009/jan/13/entertainment/et-cause13 | url = http://articles.latimes.com/2009/jan/13/entertainment/et-cause13 | title = Letting the trumpets, and electric guitars, herald Barack Obama | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2009-01-13 | work = Los Angeles Times | author = Daunt, Tina }}</ref>。音乐会免费向公众开放，还有{{lang|en|[[HBO|HBO]]}}对音乐进行开放式直播，任何人都可以通过有线电视免费收看<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.spin.com/articles/springsteen-bono-beyonce-play-obama-inaugural-concert/ | title = Springsteen, Bono, Beyonce to Play Obama Inaugural Concert | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2009-01-12 | work = Spin | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130524182136/http://www.spin.com/articles/springsteen-bono-beyonce-play-obama-inaugural-concert/ | author = Fitzmaurice, Larry | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2013-05-24 }}</ref>。估计有40万人到林肯纪念堂观看音乐会<ref name="MSSRR" />。[[華盛頓地鐵|華盛頓地鐵]]这天共计运送旅客61万6324人次，刷新1999年7月4日创下的周日载客量纪录（54万零945人）<ref name="MSSRR">{{cite news | publisher = The Washington Post Company | url = http://voices.washingtonpost.com/getthere/2009/01/metro_sets_sunday_ridership_re.html | title = Metro Sets Sunday Ridership Record | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2009-01-19 | work = The Washington Post | author = McPhate, Mike | archive-date = 2011-12-15 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20111215114252/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/getthere/2009/01/metro_sets_sunday_ridership_re.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

=== 马丁·路德·金纪念日活动 ===
2009年1月19日是就职典礼的前一天，这天正好是美国联邦假期[[马丁·路德·金纪念日|马丁·路德·金纪念日]]，纪念[[马丁·路德·金|马丁·路德·金]]的[[生日|生日]]。奥巴马呼吁各地社区遵循这一天的传统，通过提供公民志愿服务来向这位人权领袖致敬<ref name="OCfNDoS">{{cite news | title = Obama Calls for National Day of Service | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131205201300/http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/12/17/obama-calls-for-national-day-of-service/ | url = http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/12/17/obama-calls-for-national-day-of-service/ | date = 2008-12-17 | work = The New York Times | author = Seelye, Katharine Q. | publisher = The New York Times Company | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2013-12-05 }}</ref><ref name="OCMDwS" />。这一天里，全美各地一共提供了超过1.3万次社区服务，比前一年多了一倍多，是国会通过《金假期和服务法》后14年来最多的一次<ref name="KingDay">{{cite news | url = http://www.nationalservice.gov/about/newsroom/releases_detail.asp?tbl_pr_id=1213 | title = Yes We Did! 2009 King Day of Service is Largest Ever | work = Corporation for National and Community Service | date = 2009-01-23 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121010141728/http://www.nationalservice.gov/about/newsroom/releases_detail.asp?tbl_pr_id=1213 | archivedate = 2012-10-10 | deadurl = yes | accessdate = 2012-10-10 }}</ref>。

奥巴马花了一小时前往[[沃尔特·里德陆军医疗中心|沃尔特·里德陆军医疗中心]]与在[[伊拉克战争|伊拉克战争]]和[[阿富汗战争_(2001年)|阿富汗战争]]中负伤的军人及其家属见面、交谈<ref name="OCMDwS">{{cite news | author = Branigin, William and Philip Rucker | url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/19/AR2009011901189.html | title = Obama Commemorates MLK Day with Service | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2009-01-19 | work = The Washington Post | publisher = The Washington Post Company | archive-date = 2020-05-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200518045543/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/19/AR2009011901189.html | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="WvttadosOnhm">{{cite web |archivedate=2011-06-11 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110611212429/http://www.courant.com/about/chi-011909-obama-service-jan20%2C0%2C3440131.story |url=http://www.courant.com/about/chi-011909-obama-service-jan20,0,3440131.story |title=With visit to troops and day of service, Obama nears his moment |accessdate=2011-06-11 |date=2009-01-19 |work=Chicago Tribune |publisher=Hartford Courant |author=James, Frank |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。接下来，他和青少年无家可归者收容所萨沙布鲁斯之家的领袖[[马丁·路德·金三世|马丁·路德·金三世]]一起参加了其他服务活动<ref name="OCMDwS" /><ref name="WvttadosOnhm" />。

乔·拜登在哥伦比亚特区东北部的一处[[国际仁人家园|国际仁人家园]]悬挂[[干壁|干壁]]<ref name="OCMDwS" /><ref>{{cite news | title = Obama paints, hosts dinners before the big day | date = 2009-01-20 | work = USA Today | author = Wolf, Richard}}</ref>，他的夫人[[吉尔·拜登|吉尔]]和女儿阿什利（{{lang|en|Ashley}}），以及[[米歇尔·奥巴马|米歇尔·奥巴马]]和奥巴马夫妇的女儿玛丽亚与萨莎一起在[[罗伯特·F·肯尼迪体育馆|罗伯特·F·肯尼迪体育馆]]停留了一上午，帮助数千名志愿者为海外美军准备超过8.5万个[[爱心包裹|爱心包裹]]<ref name="KingDay" /><ref name="WvttadosOnhm" /><ref name="HDKLaSA">{{cite web | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131117042520/http://www.whitehouse.gov/blog/dr_king_service/ | archivedate = 2013-11-17 | url = http://www.whitehouse.gov/blog/dr_king_service/ | title = Honoring Dr. King's Legacy and Serving America | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2009-01-20 | publisher = Whitehouse.gov }}</ref>。当晚，总统当选人主持了三场相互独立的跨党派晚餐会，对[[约翰·麦凯恩|约翰·麦凯恩]]、[[克林·鲍威尔|克林·鲍威尔]]和乔·拜登的工作致谢<ref name="OCMDwS" /><ref name="WvttadosOnhm" />。

=== “儿童的就职典礼：我们就是未来” ===
2009年1月19日晚，米歇尔·奥巴马和吉尔·拜登在[[威瑞森中心|威瑞森中心]]主持了“儿童的就职典礼：我们就是未来”活动，[[麦莉·赛勒斯|麦莉·赛勒斯]]、[[黛米·洛瓦托|黛米·洛瓦托]]和[[乔纳斯兄弟|乔纳斯兄弟]]在音乐会上向军人家属致敬<ref name="MOMC" />。活动通过[[迪斯尼频道|迪斯尼频道]]和[[迪斯尼广播|迪斯尼广播]]进行直播<ref name="JBAFasaOip" />。参加演出的其他名流还包括[[鲍沃|鲍沃]]、[[乔治·洛佩兹|乔治·洛佩兹]]、[[科宾·布鲁|科宾·布鲁]]、[[奎恩·拉提法|奎恩·拉提法]]、[[比利·雷·赛勒斯|比利·雷·赛勒斯]]、[[沙奎尔·奥尼尔|沙奎尔·奥尼尔]]和[[杰米·福克斯|杰米·福克斯]]<ref name="MOMC" />。为了体现这一天的主题，米歇尔·奥巴马呼吁儿童通过参与无家可归人士收容所的志愿活动来参加公益活动，还可以探访老人、给美军士兵写信<ref name="MOMC">{{cite web | archivedate = 2012-02-13 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120213000420/http://www.wusa9.com/news/local/story.aspx?storyid=80624&catid=158 | url = http://www.wusa9.com/news/local/story.aspx?storyid=80624&catid=158 | title = Michelle Obama, Miley Cyrus: Favorites At Concert | accessdate = 2012-02-13 | date = 2009-01-20 | publisher = WUSA-TV (Washington, D.C.) | author = Cyr, Emily }}</ref>。

