首席大法官[[约翰·格洛佛·罗伯茨|约翰·格洛佛·罗伯茨]]主持奥巴马的宣誓仪式，米歇尔·奥巴马在一旁手持亚伯拉罕·林肯1861年宣誓时使用的《[[圣经|圣经]]》，贝拉克·奥巴马将手放在《圣经》上背诵总统誓辞<ref>{{cite news | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140611082011/http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/12/23/obama-to-take-oath-on-same-bible-as-lincoln/ | url = http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/12/23/obama-to-take-oath-on-same-bible-as-lincoln/ | title = Obama to Take Oath on Same Bible as Lincoln | author = Seelye, Katherine Q. | work = The New York Times | date = 2008-12-23 | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | archivedate = 2014-06-11 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141026152623/http://thehill.com/blogs/blog-briefing-room/news/other/39997-obama-to-be-sworn-in-on-lincoln-bible | archivedate = 2014-10-26 | title = Obama to be sworn in on Lincoln Bible | last = Good | first = Chris | date = 2008-12-23 | work = The Hill | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | url = http://thehill.com/blogs/blog-briefing-room/news/other/39997-obama-to-be-sworn-in-on-lincoln-bible }}</ref>。约4年前，身为联邦参议员的奥巴马曾在确认总统对罗伯茨担任美国首席大法官的提名中投下反对票，2009年的这场就职典礼也由此成为[[美国历史|美国历史]]上首次由首席大法官主持之前曾投票反对自己就任的总统当选人宣誓就职<ref name="OCJRSiRoPO">{{cite news | title = Obama, Chief Justice Roberts Stumble in Recitation of Presidential Oath: Chief Justice John Roberts officiated over his first inauguration Tuesday by swearing in President-elect Barack Obama as president of the United States. | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2009-01-20 | publisher = FOX News Network, LLC. | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131205035300/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2009/01/20/obama-chief-justice-roberts-stumble-recitation-presidential-oath/ | archivedate = 2013-12-05 | url = http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2009/01/20/obama-chief-justice-roberts-stumble-recitation-presidential-oath/ }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.nbcnews.com/id/28753348/ | title = Roberts and Obama seal deal, with a stumble: Chief Justice and new president come from vastly different perspectives | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141026153058/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/28753348/ | date = 2009-01-02 | deadurl = no | publisher = NBCNews.com | agency = Associated Press | archivedate = 2014-10-26 }}</ref>。

罗伯茨和奥巴马在背诵誓辞的过程中都出现了多处失误，根据[[美国宪法|宪法]]，总统宣誓就职的誓辞如下：
{{bquote|我庄严宣誓我一定忠实执行合众国总统职务，竭尽全力维护、保护和捍卫合众国宪法{{#tag:ref|原文为：{{lang|en|I do solemnly swear that I will faithfully execute the office of President of the United States and will to the best of my ability preserve, protect, and defend the Constitution of the United States.}}<ref name="oathflub">{{cite news | first = Pete | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090218043726/http://firstread.msnbc.msn.com/archive/2009/01/20/1751351.aspx | last = Williams | title = About That oath flub | url = http://firstread.msnbc.msn.com/archive/2009/01/20/1751351.aspx | work = MSNBC.com | date = 2009-01-20 | accessdate = 2009-02-18 | archivedate = 2009-02-18 | deadurl = yes }}</ref>|group="注"}}<ref name="USC25">{{cite book | title = 美国宪政历程：影响美国的25个司法大案 | author1 = 任东来 | author2 = 陈伟 | author3 = 白雪峰 | author4 = Charles J. McClain | author5 = Laurene Wu McClain | publisher = 中国法制出版社 | isbn = 7-80182-138-6 | pages = 565-567 | chapter = 附录二：美利坚合众国宪法|date=2004年1月}}</ref><ref name="Li1999">{{cite book | author = 李道揆 | title = 美国政府和政治（下册） | publisher = 商务印书馆 | year = 1999 | pages = 775-799 | chapter = 美利坚合众国宪法}}</ref>。}}

罗伯茨为这场就职典礼做了细心的准备，但有备忘录表明，他计划在背诵誓辞时所做的暂停方案没有在宣誓仪式开始前送到奥巴马的幕僚手中。这导致奥巴马在第一句时就意外中断了罗伯茨的引领，在罗伯茨正念到“庄严宣誓”四字时就说出了“我，贝拉克”，不过他马上就通过念出全句来予以纠正：“我，贝拉克·侯赛因·奥巴马，庄严宣誓。”{{#tag:ref|原话为：{{lang|en|I, Barack Hussein Obama, do solemnly swear.}}|group="注"}}<ref>{{cite web | last = Toobin | first = Jeffrey | title = How Obama, Roberts Interpret Laws In 'The Oath' | url = http://www.npr.org/2012/09/17/161144225/oba | work = Fresh Air (WHYY) | publisher = NPR.org | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131217090427/http://www.npr.org/2012/09/17/161144225/oba | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | date = 2012-09-17 | archivedate = 2013-12-17 | deadurl = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last = Toobin | first = Jeffrey | title = The Oath: The Obama White House and the Supreme Court | url = https://archive.org/details/oathobamawhiteho0000toob | year = 2012 | publisher = Doubleday | isbn = 978-0385527200 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/oathobamawhiteho0000toob/page/7 7]–10}}</ref>

罗伯茨没有带笔记，他把下一句中的“忠实”（{{lang|en|faithfully}}）一词错放到了“执行合众国总统职务”的后面，并且把“合众国的总统”（{{lang|en|president of United States}}）错念成了“对合众国的总统”（{{lang|en|president to United States}}）。奥巴马跟随引导念至“我一定执行”（{{lang|en|that I will execute}}）时暂时了一下，罗伯茨试图纠正自己念错的话，但出现了结巴：“总——忠于总——合众国总统。{{#tag:ref|原话为：{{lang|en|the off— faithfully the pres— the office of President of the United States.}}|group="注"}}”奥巴马接下来重复了罗伯茨之前念错的这句话。<ref name="OCJRSiRoPO" /><ref name="oathflub" /><ref>{{cite web |title=President Obama 2009 Inaugural Ceremony |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141026160555/http://www.c-span.org/video/?283479-1%2Fpresident-obama-2009-inaugural-ceremony |url=http://www.c-span.org/video/?283479-1/president-obama-2009-inaugural-ceremony |publisher=C-SPAN |accessdate=2014-10-26 |format=Video |date=2009-01-20 |archivedate=2014-10-26 }}</ref>

罗伯茨在总统誓辞最后加上了一句“愿上帝保佑你”{{#tag:ref|原话为：{{lang|en|so help you God}}|group="注"}}，奥巴马也在最后重复时念出“愿上帝保佑我”{{#tag:ref|原话为：{{lang|en|so help me God}}|group="注"}}，之前奥巴马曾主动要求在誓辞最后加上这句话<ref name="Mears">{{cite news | accessdate = 2014-10-26 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130126031020/http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2009/01/09/obama-to-asked-to-say-so-help-me-god-at-swearing-in/ | title = Obama has asked to say 'so help me God' at swearing-in | author = Mears, Bill | work = Political Ticker | publisher = Cable News Network | date = 2009-01-09 | archivedate = 2013-01-26 | url = http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2009/01/09/obama-to-asked-to-say-so-help-me-god-at-swearing-in/ }}</ref>。最后罗伯茨祝贺奥巴马成为新任美国总统<ref name="oathflub" />。

===== 第二次宣誓就职 =====
[[File:Second_oath_of_office_of_Barack_Obama.jpg|缩略图]]
总统誓辞的引导和背诵中出现的多处错误引起大量公众讨论，多名宪法学者认为奥巴马应该重新宣誓。[[波士顿大学|波士顿大学]]宪法学者杰克·比尔曼（{{lang|en|Jack Beerman}}）指出，虽然法院很可能永远都不会对此较真，但要是奥巴马是自己的当事人，自己会建议他重新宣誓，因为这毕竟是“宪法中规定他应该要说的话”<ref>{{cite news | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130530030129/http://www.sfgate.com/politics/article/Experts-say-Obama-should-retake-the-oath-3253884.php | url = http://www.sfgate.com/politics/article/Experts-say-Obama-should-retake-the-oath-3253884.php | title = Experts say Obama should retake the oath | last = Lochhead | first = Carolyn | date = 2009-01-21 | work = San Francisco Chronicle | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | archivedate = 2013-05-30 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。虽然[[白宫新闻发言人|白宫新闻发言人]][[罗伯特·吉布斯|罗伯特·吉布斯]]一度表示，奥巴马没有打算重新宣誓<ref>{{cite news | archivedate = 2014-03-23 | url = http://www.cbsnews.com/news/no-plans-for-obama-to-retake-oath/ | title = No Plans For Obama To Retake Oath | publisher = CBS News | date = 2009-01-21 | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | first = Mark | last = Knoller | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140323080913/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/no-plans-for-obama-to-retake-oath/ }}</ref>，但首席大法官罗伯茨还是同意了[[白宫法律顾问|白宫法律顾问]][[格雷格·克雷格|格雷格·克雷格]]（{{lang|en|Greg Craig}}）的请求重新主持宣誓仪式。第二次宣誓仪式于2009年1月21日晚在[[白宫|白宫]][[白宫地图室|地图室]]举行，除总统和首席大法官外，现场还有几位总统助理、[[记者|记者]]和一名白宫摄影师<ref name="NYTretake">{{cite news | publisher = The New York Times Company | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/22/us/politics/22oath.html?_r=2&scp=1&sq=oath%20of%20office%20retake&st=cse& | title = I Really Do Swear, Faithfully: Obama and Roberts Try Again | author = Zeleny, Jeff | work = The New York Times | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | date = 2009-01-21 | archivedate = 2014-10-27 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141027004331/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/22/us/politics/22oath.html?_r=2&scp=1&sq=oath%20of%20office%20retake&st=cse& }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title = Obama re-takes oath of office at the White House | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | date = 2009-01-21 | publisher = Cable News Network | work = Political Ticker | author = Mears, Bill | url = http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2009/01/21/obama-re-takes-oath-of-office-at-the-white-house/ | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141016221107/http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2009/01/21/obama-re-takes-oath-of-office-at-the-white-house/ | archivedate = 2014-10-16 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。克雷格表示，白宫最终是出于谨慎起见而决定重新进行宣誓仪式，“就职宣誓是有效的……总统宣誓就职的过程也是恰当的……但誓言（毕竟）在宪法上有明文规定”<ref name="autogenerated1">{{cite news | first = Michael D. | last = Shear | title = Obama sworn in again, with right words | url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/21/AR2009012103685.html | work = The Washington Post | date = 2009-01-22 | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | publisher = The Washington Post Company | archive-date = 2021-01-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210118155523/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/21/AR2009012103685.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。不过，第二次宣誓仪式上没有使用《圣经》<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/21/AR2009012103685.html | title = Obama Sworn in Again, With Right Words | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | date = 2009-01-22 | author = Shear, Michael D. | work = The Washington Post | publisher = The Washington Post Company | archive-date = 2021-01-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210118155523/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/21/AR2009012103685.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

==== 就职演讲 ====
{{wikisource|巴拉克·奥巴马就职演说}}
总统奥巴马就职演讲的核心主题是呼吁责任感，这其中既包括联邦政府要敢于挑起重担，也希冀普通民众勇于承担责任<ref name="Guardian">{{cite news | title = Obama inauguration: Words of history ... crafted by 27-year-old in Starbucks | url = http://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/jan/20/barack-obama-inauguration-us-speech | work = The Guardian | location = United Kingdom | date = 2009-01-20 | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | first = Ed | last = Pilkington | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131019114524/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/jan/20/barack-obama-inauguration-us-speech | archivedate = 2013-10-19 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title = Responsibility is the Theme of Obama's Inauguration Speech, Aides Say | publisher = Fox News | date = 2009-01-18 | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130518000631/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2009/01/18/responsibility-theme-obamas-inauguration-speech-aides-say/ | archivedate = 2013-05-18 | url = http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2009/01/18/responsibility-theme-obamas-inauguration-speech-aides-say/ }}</ref>。在修辞专家詹姆斯·麦金（{{lang|en|James Mackin}}）看来，奥巴马没有在演说中用语音来强调某个令人难忘的短语，而是引述美国历史上一场被刻意低估的演说来和自己即将领导的新政府联系起来<ref name="mackin">{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140710120413/http://tulane.edu/news/newwave/012309_inaugural_address.cfm |deadurl=yes |url=http://tulane.edu/news/newwave/012309_inaugural_address.cfm |title=Inaugural Speech Focuses on Tradition |work=New Wave |publisher=Tulane University |date=2009-01-23 |accessdate=2014-07-10 |archivedate=2014-07-10 }}</ref>。
