奥巴马在演讲第二段的结尾说道：“我们人民仍然保持着对先辈理想和立国文献的坚定信念”{{#tag:ref|原话为：{{lang|en|we the people have remained faithful to the ideals of our forebears and true to our founding documents.}}|group="注"}}。演讲中强调了“传统”和“遗产”这样的字眼，以及“诚信”、“勇气”和“[[爱国主义|爱国主义]]”这样的“老”价值观。总统在演讲接近尾声时引述了[[托马斯·潘恩|托马斯·潘恩]]的《[[美国危机|美国危机]]》（{{lang|en|''The American Crisis''}}），[[乔治·华盛顿|乔治·华盛顿]]当年曾下令将其内容念给自己的部队听：“我们要让将来的世界知道……在那唯有希望和勇气保持我们生存的深冬严寒里……我们的城市和国家，都会站起来迎接这个共同的危机”{{#tag:ref|原话为：{{lang|en|Let it be told to the future world ... that in the depth of winter, when nothing but hope and virtue could survive ... that the city and the country, alarmed at one common danger, came forth to meet [it].}}|group="注"}}。麦金指出，奥巴马间在竞选期曾强调美国需要变革，因此他在演讲中试图安抚民众，自己会在国家的传统范围内行使总统职权<ref name="mackin" />。

奥巴马接下来在演说中表明自己希望美国人民达到的目标：“这就是为什么我想成为人民公仆、成为更出色的政治家。这就是为什么我希望回到家并成为更优秀的父母、更好的职工、更杰出的公民。”{{#tag:ref|原话为：{{lang|en|This is why I want to go into public service and be a better politician. This is why I want to go home and be a better parent, better worker, better citizen.}}|group="注"}}<ref>{{cite book | last = Alter | first = Jonathan | title = The Promise President Obama, Year One | url = https://archive.org/details/promisepresident0000alte_p1g2 | publisher = Simon & Schuster | year = 2010 | isbn = 978-1-4391-0119-3}}</ref>

奥巴马在演讲中称，“我们现在需要的是责任感的新时代——是每个美国人（对责任）的认同”{{#tag:ref|原话为：{{lang|en|what is required of us now is a new era of responsibility—a recognition, on the part of every American}}|group="注"}}，“那些掌握着公众税款的人都要负起责任”{{#tag:ref|原话为：{{lang|en|those of us who manage the public's dollars will be held to account.}}|group="注"}}；他还引述[[歌舞片|歌舞]][[喜剧电影|喜剧片]]《[[摇摆乐时代|摇摆乐时代]]》（{{lang|en|''Swing Time''}}）中由[[杰罗姆·克恩|杰罗姆·克恩]]（{{lang|en|Jerome Kern}}）和多箩西·菲尔兹创作歌曲“{{lang|en|Pick Yourself Up}}”（意为《振作精神》）的歌词，称“从今往后，我们必须振作起来，重整旗鼓，振兴美国”<ref name="boston_globe">{{cite news | url = http://www.boston.com/news/politics/politicalintelligence/2009/01/obama_calls_for_3.html | title = Obama calls for American renewal | author = Foon Rhee | date = 2009-01-20 | accessdate = 2013-12-20 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131220033543/http://www.boston.com/news/politics/politicalintelligence/2009/01/obama_calls_for_3.html | work = The Boston Globe | archivedate = 2013-12-20 }}</ref>。前戏剧评论家，《纽约时报》专栏作家[[弗兰克·里奇|弗兰克·里奇]]（{{lang|en|Frank Rich}}）著文指出，奥巴马的演说词与菲尔兹的歌词联系起来，与当年的[[大萧条|大萧条]]形成微妙的联系<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/25/opinion/25rich.html?_r=0 | title = No time for poetry | author = Rich, Frank | date = 2009-01-25 | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | work = The New York Times | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141027040141/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/25/opinion/25rich.html?_r=0 | archivedate = 2014-10-27 | publisher = The New York Times Company }}</ref>。

奥巴马在演说中多次引用《圣经》，与“[[黑人教堂|黑人教堂]]传统”演说类似。他还强调了美国的宗教多样性，认为国家“海纳百川的传统”是一种优势，他说：“我们是一个由[[基督教|基督徒]]和穆斯林，[[犹太人|犹太人]]、[[印度教|印度教]]徒和[[无神论|无神论]]者组成的国家”{{#tag:ref|原话为：{{lang|en|We are a nation of Christians and Muslims, Jews and Hindus and non-believers.}}|group="注"}}，这也是美国总统就职演讲中首次承认美国无神论者的存在。<ref>{{cite news | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140202120749/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/religion/2009-01-20-obama-non-believers_N.htm | url = http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/religion/2009-01-20-obama-non-believers_N.htm | title = An inaugural first: Obama acknowledges 'non-believers' | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | date = 2009-01-22 | work = USA Today | author = Grossman, Cathy Lynn | archivedate = 2014-02-02 | deadurl = no }}</ref>

奥巴马的就职演讲所获评价褒贬不一，一些评论中认为演说中的克制和直言进谏的基调值得称道<ref name="WpBOia">{{cite news | url = http://articles.latimes.com/2009/jan/21/nation/na-inaug-literati21 | title = Writers praise Barack Obama's inaugural address | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | date = 2009-01-21 | work = Los Angeles Times | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140717133039/http://articles.latimes.com/2009/jan/21/nation/na-inaug-literati21 | deadurl = no | author = Reynolds, Susan Salter | archivedate = 2014-07-17 }}</ref>，还有一些认为其中太过浅薄，充斥着陈辞滥调<ref name="OIADSC">{{cite news | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/01/21/obamas-inaugural-address_n_159713.html | title = Obama's Inaugural Address Draws Some Criticism | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | date = 2009-01-21 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131109152442/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/01/21/obamas-inaugural-address_n_159713.html | work = The Huffington Post | first = Stuart | last = Whatley | archivedate = 2013-11-09 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。奥巴马在演说中态度乐观，但对前总统[[乔治·沃克·布什|小布什]]和[[比尔·克林顿|比尔·克林顿]]表现出了批评态度<ref name="WpBOia" />。《纽约时报》驻哥伦比亚特区首席通讯记者[[戴维·桑格|戴维·桑格]]（{{lang|en|David E. Sanger}}）表示，奥巴马的演说是继[[富兰克林·德拉诺·罗斯福|富兰克林·德拉诺·罗斯福]]呼吁恢复美国价值观的就职演讲以来对即将离任总统所做出的最严厉斥责<ref name="RBERV">{{cite news | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/21/us/politics/21assess.html?_r=2& | title = Rejecting Bush Era, Reclaiming Values | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | date = 2009-01-20 | work = The New York Times | publisher = The New York Times Company | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141027155235/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/21/us/politics/21assess.html?_r=2& | author = Sanger, David | archivedate = 2014-10-27 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。布什政府对这场演说中的语气感到不满，称这段演讲的基调本来应该是仪式性并且尊重他人的，但这次却转变成了一种公开性的谩骂<ref>{{cite web | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130511212337/http://themoderatevoice.com/25881/bush-team-reportedly-irked-over-obama-inaugural-address/ | url = http://themoderatevoice.com/25881/bush-team-reportedly-irked-over-obama-inaugural-address/ | title = Bush Team Reportedly Irked Over Obama Inaugural Address | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | date = 2009-01-23 | work = The Moderate Voice | author = Gandelman, Joe | archivedate = 2013-05-11 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。共和党人认为这次讲话导致国家错失了一次寻求团结的机会，不过奥巴马的[[白宫幕僚长|白宫办公厅主任]][[拉姆·伊曼纽尔|拉姆·伊曼纽尔]]则认为，这场演说不过是反映了人民的意愿<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/23/us/politics/22web-baker.html?_r=0 | title = On Plane to Texas, Critiques of the Speech | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | date = 2009-01-22 | publisher = The New York Times Company | work = The New York Times | author = Baker, Peter | archivedate = 2014-10-27 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141027155952/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/23/us/politics/22web-baker.html?_r=0 }}</ref>。一位记者在分析就职演说时指出，演说中强调了如今面临的负担和阴云密布的未来，美国人需要用文化遗产中的决心来面对这些挑战<ref>{{cite web | url = http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/Inauguration/story?id=6666797&page=1 | title = Obama's Inaugural Address: 'We Must Pick Ourselves Up': President Obama's Inaugural Address Weighted With Expectation and Promise | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | date = 2009-01-20 | publisher = ABC News | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130123144101/http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/Inauguration/story?id=6666797&page=1 | archivedate = 2013-01-23 | author = John Cochran | via = WORLD NEWS }}</ref>。

==== 祈祷 ====
奥巴马选择华理克和洛厄在就职典礼上祈祷的决定引发了争议；华理克曾经对[[同性婚姻|同性婚姻]]口诛笔伐<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.nbcnews.com/id/28733017/ | title = Gay rights protest held outside Warren church: Marchers decry pastor's selection as Obama inauguration speaker | accessdate = 2014-10-27 | date = 2009-01-19 | agency = Associated Press | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141027161045/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/28733017/ | work = NBCNEWS.com | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2014-10-27 }}</ref>，洛厄则有着[[公民权利和政治权利|民权]]活动家的背景<ref name="WLtdib">{{cite web | url = http://ncronline.org/news/politics/warren-lowery-deliver-inauguration-blessings | title = Warren, Lowery to deliver inauguration blessings | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | date = 2008-12-18 | work = National Catholic Reporter | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141027161313/http://ncronline.org/news/politics/warren-lowery-deliver-inauguration-blessings | author = Banks, Adelle M. | archivedate = 2014-10-27 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。奥巴马或华理克都没有在就职典礼期间提及任何与同性恋社群有直接关系的话题。华理克呼吁美国人民即便是在相互对抗时也要保持宽容的心态，面对异己时应保有文明的态度<ref>{{cite web | archivedate = 2012-01-12 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120112211512/http://www.dallasvoice.com/obama-doesnt-mention-gays-in-inaugural-address-but-lgbt-community-more-visible-than-ever-in-d-c-1018670.html | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | deadurl = yes | url = http://www.dallasvoice.com/obama-doesnt-mention-gays-in-inaugural-address-but-lgbt-community-more-visible-than-ever-in-d-c-1018670.html | title = Obama doesn't mention gays in Inaugural address, but LGBT community more visible than ever in D.C | date = 2011-12-26 | work = Dallas Voice | author = Keen, Lisa }}</ref>。华理克在开会祈祷时提及马丁·路德·金和耶稣，并且在[[主祷文|主祷文]]中对开会祈祷的内容进行总结<ref name="LB" />。洛厄在赐福时不无幽默之举，他在声明中表示希望大家在离开现场后能够像一个大家庭般团结一致。洛厄在赐福的最后幽默地表示，希望[[棕色人种|棕种人]]能够留下来，[[蒙古人种|黄种人]]可以更成熟，[[美洲原住民|红人]]得以出人头地，[[高加索人种|白人]]能够接受真理{{#tag:ref|原话为：{{lang|en|when brown can stick around, when yellow will be mellow, when the red man can get ahead man and when white would embrace what is right.}}|group="注"}}<ref name="LB" />。包括[[拉什·林博|拉什·林博]]在内的保守派人士对洛厄的赐福加以谴责，称赐福中引用《[[人人引吭高歌|人人引吭高歌]]》（{{lang|en|''Lift Every Voice and Sing''}}，亦俗称为“美国黑人的民族歌”）是一种[[种族主义|种族歧视]]行为<ref name="LB" /><ref name="IpspOs">{{cite web | url = http://www.worldnetdaily.com/index.php?fa=PAGE.view&pageId=86675 | title = Inaugural prayer slam prompts Obama smile: Rush Limbaugh: Lowery 'just insulted this country' | accessdate = 2009-07-08 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090708012915/http://www.worldnetdaily.com/index.php?fa=PAGE.view&pageId=86675 | date = 2009-01-20 | publisher = WorldNetDaily | author = Schilling, Chelsea | archivedate = 2009-07-08 | deadurl = yes }}</ref>，不过民主党人士没有这样的感观<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.pressreleasepoint.com/viewers-offer-mixed-reactions-reverend-lowery039s-inaugural-benediction | title = Viewers Offer Mixed Reactions to Reverend Lowery's Inaugural Benediction | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | date = 2009-01-26 | publisher = HCD Research | archive-date = 2011-10-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20111003225426/http://www.pressreleasepoint.com/viewers-offer-mixed-reactions-reverend-lowery039s-inaugural-benediction | dead-url = no }}</ref>。洛厄的话中还有一句“当[[非裔美国人|黑人]]不会再被要求从后门进入{{#tag:ref|原话为：{{lang|en|When black will not be asked to get in back.}}|group="注"}}<ref>{{cite news | title = When black will not be asked to get back | date = 2009-01-21 | work = The Economist | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | archivedate = 2014-10-28 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141028035133/http://www.economist.com/blogs/democracyinamerica/2009/01/when_black_will_not_be_asked_t | url = http://www.economist.com/blogs/democracyinamerica/2009/01/when_black_will_not_be_asked_t }}</ref>特别让林博等人感到恼火，因为在他们看来，奥巴马这天正式成为总统，这就标志着美国早已过了还会那样歧视黑人的年代<ref name="IpspOs" />。

=== 典礼过后的传统活动 ===
[[File:George_W._Bush_in_Marine_One.jpg|缩略图]]乘[[美国海军陆战队|美国海军陆战队]]直升机准备离开时看向[[美国国会大厦|美国国会大厦]]。]]
就职典礼结束后，总统奥巴马、[[第一夫人|第一夫人]]米歇尔·奥巴马、副总统乔·拜登和[[美国第二夫人|第二夫人]]吉尔·拜登陪同前总统乔治·沃克·布什和前第一夫人[[劳拉·威尔士·布什|劳拉·威尔士·布什]]从国会大厦东面离开典礼现场。为了遵循传统，奥巴马于午宴前在国会大厦总统室签署了自己第一道[[行政命令_(美国)|总统令]]<ref name="Osfpp" />，然后再在午宴的来宾簿上签字<ref name="LB" />。奥巴马的首份总统令是宣布自己就职的这一天成为“重建与和解的国庆日”<ref name="Osfpp" />，号召所有公民为彼此服务，并且为了新世纪重建祖国的共同目标服务<ref>{{cite web | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141028064028/http://www.catholic.org/news/national/story.php?id=31715 | deadurl = no | url = http://www.catholic.org/news/national/story.php?id=31715 | title = President Obama's First Presidential Proclamation | date = 2009-01-21 | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | publisher = Catholic Online | archivedate = 2014-10-28 }}</ref>。接下来，奥巴马签署命令，正式提名[[美国内阁|内阁]]和内阁附属官员交联邦国会批准<ref name="Osfpp">{{cite news | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140302065319/http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2009/01/20/obama-signs-first-presidential-proclamation/ | url = http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2009/01/20/obama-signs-first-presidential-proclamation/ | title = Obama signs first presidential proclamation | publisher = Cable News Network | date = 2009-01-20 | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2014-03-02 }}</ref>。然后，奥巴马和拜登夫妇出席在国会大厦举行的就职午宴，之后再前往白宫的总统观礼台观看游行。

==== 午宴 ====
前总统布什及夫人准备返回德克萨斯州的老家，奥巴马和拜登夫妇与多位国会议员宾客一起参加在国会大厦[[国家雕像大厅|国家雕像大厅]]举行的就职午宴。宴会宾客包括最有影响力的国会议员和多位前总统、副总统。为了纪念[[亚伯拉罕·林肯诞辰200周年委员会|亚伯拉罕·林肯诞辰200周年]]，午宴时使用的红色和白色[[瓷器|瓷器]]是当年林肯入主白宫时那些瓷器的复制品。<ref name="thehill">{{cite news | first = Mike | last = Soraghan | title = Obama's Inauguration makes tourists out of lawmakers | url = http://thehill.com/leading-the-news/obamas-inauguration-makes-tourists-out-of-lawmakers-2009-01-20.html | publisher = Capitol Hill Publishing Corp. | work = The Hill | date = 2009-01-20 | accessdate = 2009-01-23 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090123043500/http://thehill.com/leading-the-news/obamas-inauguration-makes-tourists-out-of-lawmakers-2009-01-20.html | archivedate = 2009-01-23 }}</ref>
[[File:2009_Obama_inauguration_luncheon.jpg|缩略图]]国家雕像大厅向参加就职午宴的宾客演说]]

从1953年开始，在国会大厦举行午宴就成为总统就职典礼的标准程序，在此以前，午宴通常是在白宫举行，并由即将离任的总统和第一夫人主持。就职午餐的菜单上通常会有新总统和副总统故乡州的特色菜式，2009年的菜色就包括焖海鲜、鸭和[[野鸡|野鸡]]作为主菜，再配上[[黑比诺|黑比诺]]酒，甜点则是苹果肉桂[[海绵蛋糕|海绵蛋糕]]配上甜奶油[[蜜饯|糖霜]]。从1985年起，主桌的后方就会挂有一幅画作为背景，2009年的就职午宴主桌背景画作是[[托马斯·希尔|托马斯·希尔]]（{{lang|en|Thomas Hill}}）于1865年创作的《优胜美地山谷的景观》（{{lang|en|''View of the Yosemite Valley''}}），这幅画是纪念林肯总统于1864年签署特许状建立[[优胜美地国家公园|优胜美地国家公园]]，这是联邦政府首次把公园用地保护起来作为公共用途。<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.inaugural.senate.gov/luncheon/ | title = Inauguration of the President: Luncheon | publisher = United States Congress Joint Congressional Committee on Inaugural Ceremonies | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141025114035/http://www.inaugural.senate.gov/luncheon | archivedate = 2014-10-25 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://inaugural.senate.gov/history/daysevents/inauguralluncheon.cfm | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121006180449/http://inaugural.senate.gov/history/daysevents/inauguralluncheon.cfm | title = Inaugural Luncheon | publisher = United States Congress Joint Congressional Committee on Inaugural Ceremonies | accessdate = 2012-10-06 | archivedate = 2012-10-06 | deadurl = yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | archivedate = 2012-10-06 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121006205742/http://inaugural.senate.gov/luncheon/painting.cfm | deadurl = yes | url = http://inaugural.senate.gov/luncheon/painting.cfm | title = 2009 Painting: 'View of the Yosemite Valley' | publisher = United States Congress Joint Congressional Committee on Inaugural Ceremonies | accessdate = 2012-10-06 }}</ref>

联邦参议员[[泰德·肯尼迪|泰德·肯尼迪]]在午宴期间出现抽搐并晕倒，他立即被送到医院接受治疗<ref>{{cite news | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140911123346/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/28755439/ | url = http://www.nbcnews.com/id/28755439/ | title = Kennedy released from hospital after seizure: Aide: His spirits are good; doctors want him to get some rest | work = NBCNews.com | date = 2009-01-21 | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | archivedate = 2014-09-11 | deadurl = no | agency = Associated Press }}</ref><ref name="SKCALFO">{{cite web | archivedate = 2014-09-11 | url = http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=99614326 | title = Sen. Kennedy Collapses at Luncheon For Obama | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | publisher = National Public Radio | date = 2009-01-20 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140911063052/http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=99614326 }}</ref>。起初有报道中错误地声称最年长的与会联邦参议员[[罗伯特·伯德|罗伯特·伯德]]也在午宴时病倒<ref>{{cite news | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140911161202/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1124868/Ted-Kennedy-recovering-suffering-convulsions-Obama-inaugural-lunch.html | archivedate = 2014-09-11 | deadurl = no | title = Ted Kennedy recovering after suffering convulsions at Obama inaugural lunch | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | date = 2009-01-21 | publisher = The Daily Mail (United Kingdom) | location = London | first = Liz | last = Hazelton | url = http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1124868/Ted-Kennedy-recovering-suffering-convulsions-Obama-inaugural-lunch.html }}</ref>，之后证实这些报道内容有误<ref name="SKCALFO" />，对此伯德表示，肯尼迪是他长年的好友，看到朋友在现场晕倒让伯德感到不安，因此之后也离开了<ref>{{cite news | archivedate = 2014-09-11 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140911074350/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/01/20/ted-kennedy-collapsed-at_n_159415.html | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/01/20/ted-kennedy-collapsed-at_n_159415.html | title = Ted Kennedy Collapsed at Obama Inaugural Luncheon | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | date = 2009-01-20 | work = The Huffington Post | first = Rachel | last = Weiner }}</ref>。

==== 游行 ====
