==== 国家祈祷会 ====
2009年1月21日，总统奥巴马、第一夫人米歇尔·奥巴马，副总统拜登与第二夫人吉尔齐聚[[华盛顿国家座堂|华盛顿国家座堂]]参加祷告国庆日<ref name="prayservice">{{cite web | first = Amanda | last = Ruggeri | work = U.S. News & World Report | title = For President Obama, a Somber, Inclusive Inaugural Prayer Service | date = 2009-01-21 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130622034849/http://www.usnews.com/news/obama/articles/2009/01/21/for-president-obama-a-somber-inclusive-inaugural-prayer-service | archivedate = 2013-06-22 | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | url = http://www.usnews.com/news/obama/articles/2009/01/21/for-president-obama-a-somber-inclusive-inaugural-prayer-service }}</ref>。祈祷仪式上，前总统比尔·克林顿和夫人希拉里·克林顿前来与奥巴马和拜登夫妇一起坐在前排，希拉里还会在同日晚些时候宣誓就任[[美国国务卿|国务卿]]<ref name="prayservice" /><ref name="OHFFDOTSC">{{cite news | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141028153623/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/22/us/politics/22obamacnd.html?_r=0 | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/22/us/politics/22obamacnd.html?_r=0 | title = On His First Full Day, Obama Tackles Sobering Challenges | accessdate = 2009-01-28 | date = 2009-01-21 | work = The New York Times | author = Knowlton, Brian | archivedate = 2014-10-28 | deadurl = no | publisher = The New York Times Company }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140817132945/http://www.cnn.com/2009/POLITICS/01/21/clinton.confirmation/index.html | url = http://www.cnn.com/2009/POLITICS/01/21/clinton.confirmation/index.html | title = Hillary Clinton sworn in as secretary of state | date = 2009-01-22 | publisher = Cable News Network | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | archivedate = 2014-08-17 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。出席祈祷仪式的还有约3200名接受邀请的宾客，其中包括国会议员、外交官及其他政要<ref name="prayersvc">{{cite news | author = Boorstein, Michelle | date = 2009-01-22 | publisher = The Washington Post Company | url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/21/AR2009012101029.html | title = Variety of clergy, worship program reflect a focus on inclusiveness | work = The Washington Post | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | archive-date = 2020-05-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200518033704/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/21/AR2009012101029.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。
[[File:National_Prayer_Service_Obama_Inauguration.jpg|缩略图]]

这次祈祷会有着多种信仰的主题，反映出宗教的包容性和多样性，其中既有[[新教|新教]]牧师、女性[[印度教|印度教徒]]和[[穆斯林|穆斯林]]宗教领袖，又有[[犹太教|犹太教]][[拉比|拉比]]、[[天主教会|天主教]]和[[美国圣公会|圣公会]]主教，整个仪式期间，他们念诵经文并进行祈祷。仪式上的祈祷活动引用了1789年乔治·华盛顿就职祈祷会和1865年亚伯拉罕·林肯就职演说的内容，其中包括“不要以怨恨相对，应以慈悲为怀”。{{#tag:ref|原文为：{{lang|en|with malice toward none, with charity for all.}}|group="注"}}<ref name="prayersvc" />[[基督会|基督会]]首位女性领袖、牧师莎朗·沃特金斯（{{lang|en|Sharon E. Watkins}}）在就职祈祷仪式上讲道，她也是首位在总统就职祈祷仪式上讲道的女性<ref>{{cite news | first = Laurie | last = Goodstein | title = Obama Names Minister to Lead Prayer Service | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/11/us/politics/11minister.html | work = The New York Times | date = 2009-01-10 | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | publisher = The New York Times Company | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121113135106/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/11/us/politics/11minister.html | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2012-11-13 }}</ref>。沃特金斯在讲道时引用了扎根于不同宗教的内容，如印度教、犹太教、穆斯林和[[切罗基人|切罗基人]]信仰等<ref name="prayersvc" />。

== 非正式活动 ==
除了正式活动外，许多团体和支持者还在哥伦比亚特区及周边地区举行了多场集会和庆祝活动，时间上既有就职典礼前数天，也有次日夜晚<ref name="schedule">{{cite news | title = Obama Inauguration Schedule | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131109105541/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/01/14/obama-inauguration-schedu_0_n_157859.html | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/01/14/obama-inauguration-schedu_0_n_157859.html | agency = Associated Press | work = The Huffington Post | date = 2009-01-24 | accessdate = 2014-10-28 | archivedate = 2013-11-09 }}</ref>。其中一场为史无前例的“人民就职舞会”，旨在为全美各地经济困难或肢体不便的普通百姓提供参与就职庆典的机会，如果没有这场舞会，他们都将无法亲身参与到这一系列盛会之中<ref name="wp2">{{cite news | first = Avis | last = Thomas-Lester | title = Preparing for the Ball of a Lifetime | publisher = The Washington Post Company | url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/story/2009/01/19/ST2009011900765.html | work = The Washington Post | date = 2009-01-01 | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | archive-date = 2020-05-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200518002243/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/story/2009/01/19/ST2009011900765.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。弗吉尼亚州[[费尔法克斯县_(弗吉尼亚州)|费尔法克斯县]]生意人厄尔·斯塔福德（{{lang|en|Earl W. Stafford}}）通过家族基金花费了约160万美元将约300名客人带到哥伦比亚特区，舞会于2009年1月19日举行，共有约450人参加<ref name="wp2" /><ref>{{cite news | author = Thomas-Lester, Avis | date = 2009-01-21 | title = Businessman's gift stirs "platinum-level guests." | work = The Washington Post | url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/20/AR2009012004154_2.html?sid=ST2009012003848&s_pos= | accessdate = 2009-02-13 | publisher = The Washington Post Company | archive-date = 2017-09-16 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170916030711/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/20/AR2009012004154_2.html?sid=ST2009012003848&s_pos= | dead-url = no }}</ref>。舞会主办方还向获得邀请的客人提供了礼服、鞋、燕尾服和酒店客房<ref name="afpgoogle">{{cite news | title = Fairy godfather invites disadvantaged to inaugural ball | publisher = Agence France-Presse | date = 2009-01-19}}</ref>。

