te = 2014-10-29 | publisher = The Washington Post Company | url = http://voices.washingtonpost.com/inauguration-watch/2009/01/user_photos_of_d_st_problems_c.html | archive-date = 2012-10-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121005175039/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/inauguration-watch/2009/01/user_photos_of_d_st_problems_c.html | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="WP-Constable-Ticket Troubles-2009-01-21">{{cite news | title = Ticket and Travel Troubles Cloud Inauguration Success | date = 2009-01-22 | accessdate = 2009-01-22 | last = Constable | first = Pamela; Sheridan, Mary Beth | work = The Washington Post | page = A01 | url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/21/AR2009012104248.html?sid=ST2009012003386&s_pos= | archive-date = 2012-11-11 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121111093710/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/21/AR2009012104248.html?sid=ST2009012003386&s_pos= | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="purpleTunnel">{{cite news | title = Surviving the Purple Tunnel of Doom: Ticketed paradegoers stranded in tunnel | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | date = 2009-01-21 | publisher = NBCUniversal Media, LLC | work = NBC Washington | url = http://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/Surviving-the-Purple-Tunnel-of-Doom.html | location = Washington, D.C. | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2014-02-19 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140219165236/http://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/Surviving-the-Purple-Tunnel-of-Doom.html }}</ref>。联邦参议员黛安·范士丹以就职典礼国会联合委员会主席的职权针对受影响持票人士的投诉展开调查<ref name="WP-Nakamura-2009-02-21">{{cite news | title = Sen. Feinstein Launches Investigation into Ticket Fiasco | first = David A. | last = Nakamura | work = The Washington Post | date = 2009-01-21 | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | url = http://voices.washingtonpost.com/inauguration-watch/2009/01/sen_feinstein_launches_investi.html | publisher = The Washington Post Company | archive-date = 2012-10-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121005175129/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/inauguration-watch/2009/01/sen_feinstein_launches_investi.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。委员会之后宣布，所以未能入场观看典礼的持票人士将获得出席宣誓仪式的请柬和日程副本，还有总统奥巴马和副总统拜登的照片，以及就职典礼的彩色印刷品<ref name = "Blocked-ticketholders">{{cite news | url = http://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/No-Consolation-Blocked-Ticket-Holders-Get-Parting-Gifts.html | title = No Consolation: Parting gifts for blocked ticket holders | last = Stabley | first = Matthew | date = 2009-01-29 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140415080315/http://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/No-Consolation-Blocked-Ticket-Holders-Get-Parting-Gifts.html | publisher = WRC-TV | location = Washington, D.C. | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2014-04-15 }}</ref>。

=== 安保 ===
与2001年的第54届总统就职典礼和2005年的第55届总统就职典礼一样，2009年的第56届总统就职典礼也属于[[国家特别安保活动|国家特别安保活动]]，[[美国特勤局|美国特勤局]]因此在总体安保规划的制定和实施里都属于占主导地位的联邦机构<ref>Title 18 United States Code, Section 3056</ref>，[[联邦调查局|联邦调查局]]是首要的联邦反恐、情况和刑事侦察机构，联邦紧急事物管理局则是在发生任何[[恐怖主义|恐怖主义]]袭击、自然灾害或是其它任何灾难性事件后的首要联邦危机处理机构。[[美国国会警察|美国国会警察]]主要负责国会大厦和宣誓天台以及就职午宴的安保和应急响应工作。将此届总统就职典礼指定为国家特别安保活动的决定于2008年12月10日由[[美国国土安全部|美国国土安全部]][[美国国土安全部长|部长]][[迈克尔·切尔托夫|迈克尔·切尔托夫]]做出。<ref>Homeland Security Presidential Directive (HSPD) 7</ref>就职典礼的举办地点自[[九一一袭击事件|九一一袭击事件]]发生后多年来安保程度已有显著提高，考虑到就职典礼活动会给哥伦比亚特区带来的人流规模，组织者对公共安全和安保问题也更加重视。[[美国陆军|美国陆军]][[上将_(美国)|上将]]理查德·罗（{{lang|en|Richard Rowe}}）是哥伦比亚特区联合军事工作组负责人，他认为安保部队必须运用自己的想象力来预测那些之前会认为无法想象的安保威胁，特别是在2008年11月[[印度|印度]][[孟买|孟买]]发生[[2008年孟买连环恐怖袭击|连环恐怖袭击]]之后<ref>{{cite news | archivedate = 2013-06-15 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130615043718/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2009-01-19/obama-security-team-prepared-for-unthinkable/270732 | url = http://www.abc.net.au/news/2009-01-19/obama-security-team-prepared-for-unthinkable/270732 | title = Obama security team 'prepared for unthinkable' | date = 2009-01-19 | publisher = Australian Broadcasting News | accessdate = 2014-10-29 }}</ref>。有关部门提高了对恐怖分子袭击的警惕程度<ref>{{cite news | publisher = The New York Times Company | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2010/01/17/magazine/17Terror-t.html?ref=magazine | title = Obama's War Over Terror | author = Baker, Peter | accessdate = 2010-01-18 | date = 2009-01-04 | work = The New York Times | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20100204065858/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/01/17/magazine/17Terror-t.html?ref=magazine | archivedate = 2010-02-04 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。
[[File:National_Guard_at_2009_Inauguration.JPG|缩略图]]在哥伦比亚特区街头待命。]]

哥伦比亚特区的警卫临时性地翻一了番，得到来自美国各地的约8000名警察补充。有约1000名联邦调查局探员在活动安保工作方面对警察提供协助<ref name="SCEBHfIaBI" /><ref name="OsflOip" />，整个活动区域内到处都布署了美国特勤局的隐蔽反狙击人员<ref name="CNN">{{cite news | url = http://edition.cnn.com/2009/US/01/19/sniper.training/ | title = Secret Service countersnipers hunt for real snipers | publisher = Cable News Network | date = 2009-01-19 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141029140852/http://edition.cnn.com/2009/US/01/19/sniper.training/ | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | author = Meserve, Jeanne and Mike M. Ahlers | archivedate = 2014-10-29 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。[[美国运输安全管理局|运输安全管理局]]从全国调派了300余名官员协助特勤局对进入国家广场的与会人员进行安全检查<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.tsa.gov/press/happenings/2009_inauguration.shtm | title = TSA Helps Secure Inauguration | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090510123416/https://www.tsa.gov/press/happenings/2009_inauguration.shtm | accessdate = 2009-05-10 | date = 2009-01-21 | publisher = U.S. Transportation Security Administration/U.S. Department of Homeland Security | deadurl = yes | archivedate = 2009-05-10 }}</ref>。现场有约1万名国民警卫队员，其中5000人执行安保工作，1300名未经武装的队员协助[[美国公园警察|公园警察]]在国家广场管控人群；1–175[[步兵|步兵]]{{lang|en|C}}连在西北哥伦比亚特区第7街路口执行安保任务，这里是国家广场第一和第二公共视野区域之间的地带，剩下的人员则负责其他安保任务<ref name="OtcIlyb" />。[[美国联邦航空管理局|美国联邦航空管理局]]于2009年1月20日上午10点到下午18点间对哥伦比亚特区实行额外的空域限制<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.faa.gov/news/media/public_advisory_inauguration_2009.pdf | title = Flight Advisory National Security Event: 2009 Presidential Pre-Inauguration Festivities | year = 2009 | publisher = U.S. Federal Aviation Administration | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | format = [[PDF|PDF]] | archivedate = 2012-10-22 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121022033752/http://www.faa.gov/news/media/public_advisory_inauguration_2009.pdf }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/pinoy-migration/01/19/09/lockdown-set-obamas-inauguration | title = Lockdown set for Obama's inauguration | date = 2006-01-19 | publisher = ABS-CBN News (Philippines) | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120924075849/http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/pinoy-migration/01/19/09/lockdown-set-obamas-inauguration | archivedate = 2012-09-24 | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2014-10-29 }}</ref>。[[美国国防部长|国防部长]][[罗伯特·盖茨|罗伯特·盖茨]]成为[[指定幸存者|指定幸存者]]，以确保灾难性事件发生后仍能保持政府的连续性，就职典礼当天，盖茨身在哥伦比亚特区外的一处军事设施内<ref>{{cite news | title = Defense Secretary Will Skip Inauguration | url = http://voices.washingtonpost.com/44/2009/01/20/defense_secretary_will_skip_in.html?wprss=44 | work = The Washington Post | date = 2009-01-20 | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | publisher = The Washington Post Company | archive-date = 2012-10-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121005175134/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/44/2009/01/20/defense_secretary_will_skip_in.html?wprss=44 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

就职典礼当天，见证宣誓仪式以及参与游行的群众都没有人遭到逮捕。据负责安全管理的高级联邦探员称，考虑到有近200万人齐聚哥伦比亚特区，但却没有任何机构在就职典礼活动期间拘捕任何人，这个纪录是空前的<ref name="Washington Post" /><ref>{{cite news | first = James Gordon | last = Meek | title = Security withstands record crowds during President Obama's inauguration parade, swearing-in ceremony | publisher = The New York Daily News | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140923231528/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/security-withstands-record-crowds-president-obama-inauguration-parade-swearing-in-ceremony-article-1.423966 | archivedate = 2014-09-23 | deadurl = no | url = http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/security-withstands-record-crowds-president-obama-inauguration-parade-swearing-in-ceremony-article-1.423966 | work = NYDailyNews.com | date = 2009-01-20 | accessdate = 2014-10-29 }}</ref>。作家兼新闻工作者[[罗纳德·凯斯勒|罗纳德·凯斯勒]]（{{lang|en|Ronald Kessler}}）在2009年的著作《总统的特警局》（{{lang|en|''In the President's Secret Service''}}）中声称，情报部门获悉，可能会有与[[索马里青年党|索马里青年党]]有关联的个人试图针对就职典礼实行破坏活动，该组织是[[索马里|索马里]]的一个[[伊斯兰主义|伊斯兰主义者]]叛乱组织。对此，就职游行                                                                                                               路线沿途布署了十余个反狙击手小组，安保部门还审查了在附近工作的市民以及来宾的犯罪纪录，但事实证明这只是虚惊一场。凯斯纳的书中还提及了安保工作中存在的多处不足，如上百名大额竞选损助者和贵宾都没有接受安全检查就登上了“安全”大巴<ref>{{cite news | last = Harnden | first = Toby | title = Barack Obama faces 30 death threats a day, stretching US Secret Service | location = London | work = The Daily Telegraph | date = 2009-08-03 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140914145455/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/barackobama/5967942/Barack-Obama-faces-30-death-threats-a-day-stretching-US-Secret-Service.html | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | archivedate = 2014-09-14 | url = http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/barackobama/5967942/Barack-Obama-faces-30-death-threats-a-day-stretching-US-Secret-Service.html }}</ref>。

