=== 电视观众 ===
根据[[尼尔森收视率|尼尔森收视率]]调查的数量，美国最大的56个媒体市场中有30.1%的电视机转台收看就职典礼，这一[[收视率|收视率]]与2005年小布什的就职典礼相比已经翻了近一番，是继[[罗纳德·里根|罗纳德·里根]]1981年的就职典礼以来最高的一次<ref>{{cite news | title = Obama gets highest TV ratings since Reagan, sets web records | last = Bensinger | first = Greg | date = 2009-01-21 | work = Deseret News | location = Salt Lake City, UT | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | archivedate = 2012-01-19 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120119210128/http://www.deseretnews.com/article/705279305/Obama-gets-highest-TV-ratings-since-Reagan-sets-web-records.html | deadurl = no | url = http://www.deseretnews.com/article/705279305/Obama-gets-highest-TV-ratings-since-Reagan-sets-web-records.html }}</ref><ref name="neilsen-total">{{cite news | title = Updated Obama inaugural events viewed by 30.1% in top markets | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | date = 2009-01-21 | work = Nielsen Wire | archivedate = 2014-09-11 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140911181226/http://www.nielsen.com/us/en/insights/news/2009/obama-inaugural-events-viewed-by-292-in-top-markets.html | url = http://www.nielsen.com/us/en/insights/news/2009/obama-inaugural-events-viewed-by-292-in-top-markets.html }}</ref>。[[罗利_(北卡罗莱纳州)|罗利]]到[[德罕_(北卡罗莱纳州)|德罕]]的媒体市场有多达51%的家庭收看了这天的活动，是全部主要媒体市场中比例最高的，这部分是因为当地的暴风雪使得更多人选择待在室内，同时这些地区的非裔美国人数量也很高<ref name="neilsen-snow">{{cite news | title = Nielsen: Raleigh-Durham has top ratings for Obama inauguration | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | date = 2009-01-21 | work = Triangle Business Journal | archivedate = 2014-09-11 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140911053440/http://www.bizjournals.com/triangle/stories/2009/01/19/daily28.html | deadurl = no | url = http://www.bizjournals.com/triangle/stories/2009/01/19/daily28.html }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140911142958/http://www.sfgate.com/politics/article/Nearly-38-million-watched-inaugural-on-TV-3175192.php | url = http://www.sfgate.com/politics/article/Nearly-38-million-watched-inaugural-on-TV-3175192.php | title = Nearly 38 million watched inaugural on TV | last = Garofoli | first = Joe | date = 2009-01-22 | work = San Francisco Chronicle | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | archivedate = 2014-09-11 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。收视率最高的十大媒体市场中有4个在北卡罗莱纳州，两个在弗吉尼亚州，一个在马里兰州，哥伦比亚特区则在所有主要媒体市场中位居第二<ref name="neilsen-total" />。此外，由于就职典礼的日期是工作日，因此全美各地的许多学校和工作场所都允许学生和雇员收看就职典礼<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.wdsu.com/news/18514439/detail.html | title = Workplaces Plan For Inauguration Viewing | accessdate = 2012-03-08 | date = 2009-01-19 | publisher = WDSU-TV | location = New Orleans, LA | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120308220655/http://www.wdsu.com/news/18514439/detail.html | deadurl = yes | archivedate = 2012-03-08 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | work = Memphis Commercial Appeal | author = Stout, Cathryn | url = http://www.commercialappeal.com/news/local-news/schools-consider-jan-20-tv-time | title = Schools consider allowing students to watch Obama inauguration | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | date = 2009-01-06 | archivedate = 2014-09-11 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140911153505/http://www.commercialappeal.com/news/local-news/schools-consider-jan-20-tv-time | deadurl = no }}</ref>。

美国东部时间上午10点到下午17点，奥巴马就职典礼活动在17个广播和有线电视频道收获的平均收视人数达3780万，这其中还不包括[[在线和离线|在线]]观看视频流媒体直播的观众。不过这一数字与1981年-{}-里根的就职庆典相比仍然不及，当时的庆祝活动单在[[美国广播公司|美国广播公司]]、[[哥伦比亚广播公司|哥伦比亚广播公司]]和[[全国广播公司|全国广播公司]]三大电视网的平均收视人数就有4180万。<ref name="viewers">{{cite news | title = Barack Obama's inauguration watched by 40m Americans | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | date = 2009-01-22 | work = The Guardian | location = United Kingdom | author = Luft, Oliver | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130905164055/http://www.theguardian.com/media/2009/jan/22/ustelevision-barackobama | url = http://www.theguardian.com/media/2009/jan/22/ustelevision-barackobama | archivedate = 2013-09-05 | deadurl = no }}</ref>

对[[欧洲|欧洲]]电视收视情况进行调查的结果表明，[[德国|德国]]关注奥巴马就职的人数最多，吸收了1100万观众，其次是[[法国|法国]]的700万人和[[英国|英国]]的510万人<ref>{{cite news | title = Reagan Beats Obama in Inaugural Ratings, Nielsen Says | last = Pedraza | first = Rick | date = 2009-01-22 | publisher = Newsmax Media | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120825075713/http://www.newsmax.com/InsideCover/obama-inaugural-reagan/2009/01/23/id/327811 | deadurl = no | url = http://www.newsmax.com/InsideCover/obama-inaugural-reagan/2009/01/23/id/327811/ | archivedate = 2012-08-25 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title = Barack Obama's inauguration draws 37.8M, second only to Reagan's | last = Collins | first = Joel | date = 2009-01-21 | work = The Angeles Times | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121025084432/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/showtracker/2009/01/barack-obamas-i.html | url = http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/showtracker/2009/01/barack-obamas-i.html | archivedate = 2012-10-25 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。根据[[英国广播公司|英国广播公司]]的统计，英国有650万观众收看了该公司傍晚新闻节目中有关这场就职典礼的精选内容<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.theguardian.com/media/2009/jan/22/tv-ratings-barack-obama-inauguration | title = TV ratings: Barack Obama inauguration draws 5m viewers to BBC1 | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | date = 2009-01-22 | work = The Guardian | location = United Kingdom | first = Caitlin | last = Fitzsimmons | archivedate = 2013-09-05 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130905164054/http://www.theguardian.com/media/2009/jan/22/tv-ratings-barack-obama-inauguration | deadurl = no }}</ref>。

=== 互联网流量 ===
奥巴马的首次就职典礼导致新闻和社交网站的互联网流量激增，并且[[流媒体|流媒体]]的数量也创下新纪录。{{lang|en|[[CNN|CNN]]}}报道称，截至美国东部时间当天下午15点30分，与就职典礼活动有关的流媒体视频就已突破2100万段，创下历史最高纪录，这天的[[单页点阅率|单页点阅率]]达1.36亿次<ref name="internet-traffic" />。据英国广播公司报道，该公司网站上进行的实况转播在汹涌的观看流量浪潮中一度停机，巨大的流量负担导致其视频流中断了30分钟之久，打开网页的用户只能看到“请稍候再访问”（{{lang|en|Please come back later}}）的字样<ref>{{cite news | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141029154250/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/barackobama/4301367/Barack-Obama-inauguration-record-demand-crashes-BBCs-live-internet-feed.html | archivedate = 2014-10-29 | deadurl = no | url = http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/barackobama/4301367/Barack-Obama-inauguration-record-demand-crashes-BBCs-live-internet-feed.html | title = Barack Obama inauguration: record demand crashes BBC's live internet feed | last = Irvine | first = Chris | date = 2009-01-20 | work = The Daily Telegraph | location = United Kingdom | accessdate = 2014-10-29 }}</ref>。

{{lang|en|[[Akamai|Akamai]]}}科技公司的数据显示，新闻网站在不到一分钟的时间里就有540万1250人登录，是该公司开始对这些数据进行追踪以来新闻网站类别中第5高的一次<ref name="internet-traffic">{{cite news | last = Luft | first = Oliver | title = Web traffic soars for Obama inauguration | accessdate = 2009-01-22 | date = 2009-01-23 | work = The Guardian | location = United Kingdom | archivedate = 2013-09-05 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130905164044/http://www.theguardian.com/media/2009/jan/22/barack-obama-inauguration-web-traffic-soars | url = http://www.theguardian.com/media/2009/jan/22/barack-obama-inauguration-web-traffic-soars }}</ref>。使用率达到高峰时，新闻网站同时提供700万段视频流播放，创下{{lang|en|[[Akamai|Akamai]]}}测得的同时播放视频流片段数量新纪录<ref>{{cite news | title = News Sites Struggle to Stream Obama Video | accessdate = 2014-10-29 | date = 2009-01-20 | work = The New York Times | author = Vance, Ashlee | publisher = The New York Times Company | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140106140553/http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/01/20/news-sites-struggle-to-stream-obamas-innaguration-speech/ | archivedate = 2014-01-06 | url = http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/01/20/news-sites-struggle-to-stream-obamas-innaguration-speech/ }}</ref>。除了互联网观众人数创下美国总统就职典礼的新纪录外，2009年奥巴马的就职典礼活动还在宣誓仪式的[[网络直播|网络直播]]中提供了实时音频介绍和[[隐藏字幕|隐藏字幕]]，这在历史上均属首次<ref name="webcast" />。

== 国际反应 ==
[[File:Kenyans_observing_Barack_Obama's_2009_Inaugural_Address.jpg|250px]][[奈洛比|奈洛比]]的[[美国驻外机构列表|美国大使馆]]坐满了前来观看就职典礼的肯尼亚人]]
[[国际社会|国际社会]]对贝拉克·奥巴马就职典礼的关注度是前所未有的。世界多个不同国家和地区的居民，或是生活在这些国家的美国[[侨民|侨民]]中通过电视直播或互联网观看就职典礼的人数需以百万来计算。部分国家的收视人数可与[[2008年夏季奥林匹克运动会开幕式|2008年夏季奥林匹克运动会开幕式]]平分秋色。<ref name="kdn" />

世界各地通过各种各样的方式庆祝这场就职典礼，称颂这一事件的历史意义，并祝贺奥巴马当选。肯尼亚是奥巴马父亲的故国，当地居民将就职庆典作为公众假期来庆祝<ref>{{cite news | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/7833101.stm | title = TV row over Kenya Obama 'junket' | accessdate = 2014-10-30 | date = 2009-01-16 | work = BBC | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140701131006/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/7833101.stm | archivedate = 2014-07-01 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。[[雅加达|雅加达]]的美国侨民和[[印度尼西亚|印度尼西亚]]人在午夜免费舞会上观看就职典礼，并且还有雅加达01国立小学的学生表演，奥巴马儿时曾在该校就读<ref name="usa2day">{{cite news | first = Zoe | last = Aslop | title = Kenyans' inaugural trip to USA riles some at home | archivedate = 2014-10-30 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141030142737/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/world/2009-01-19-worldinauguration_N.htm | url = http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/world/2009-01-19-worldinauguration_N.htm | work = USA Today | date = 2009-01-19 | accessdate = 2014-10-30 }}</ref>。[[日本|日本]]的[[小滨市|小滨市]]燃放焰火来庆祝奥巴马就职，寺院内还有撞钟，并且有人跳起了草裙舞<ref name="WSJBlogJapan">{{cite news | first = Miho | last = Inada | title = Early Inauguration Celebration in Obama, Japan | url = http://blogs.wsj.com/washwire/2009/01/20/early-inauguration-celebration-in-obama-japan/ | work = The Wall Street Journal | publisher = Dow Jones & Company, Inc. | date = 2009-01-21 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140709123637/http://blogs.wsj.com/washwire/2009/01/20/early-inauguration-celebration-in-obama-japan/ | archivedate = 2014-07-09 | accessdate = 2014-10-30 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.nbcnews.com/id/28753038/displaymode/1107/s/2/framenumber/21/ | title = "Photo:Obama girls" dance the hula to celebrate the inauguration of President Barack Obama | author = Ota, Kiyoshi | date = 2009-01-21 | accessdate = 2014-10-30 | work = MSNBC.com | archive-date = 2014-01-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140106041102/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/28753038/displaymode/1107/s/2/framenumber/21/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。[[加拿大总督|加拿大总督]][[庄美楷|庄美楷]]和[[加拿大总理|总理]][[史蒂芬·哈珀|史蒂芬·哈珀]]代表加拿大人民表示祝贺<ref>{{cite web | title = Statement by Prime Minister Stephen Harper | accessdate = 2014-10-30 | date = 2009-01-20 | publisher = Office of the Prime Minister of Canada | archivedate = 2014-01-18 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140118214259/http://www.pm.gc.ca/eng/news/2009/01/20/statement-prime-minister-canada-inauguration-barack-obama-44th-president-united | url = http://www.pm.gc.ca/eng/news/2009/01/20/statement-prime-minister-canada-inauguration-barack-obama-44th-president-united }}</ref>，[[墨西哥总统|墨西哥总统]][[费利佩·卡尔德龙|费利佩·卡尔德龙]]祝福奥巴马“在新任美国总统的位置上取得伟大的成功”<ref name="worldcongrats">{{cite news | title = World congratulates Obama on taking office | date = 2009-01-21 | publisher = Cable News Network | accessdate = 2014-10-30 | archivedate = 2013-01-25 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130125015435/http://edition.cnn.com/2009/POLITICS/01/20/obama.international.reaction/index.html | url = http://edition.cnn.com/2009/POLITICS/01/20/obama.international.reaction/index.html }}</ref>。[[以色列|以色列]][[以色列总统|总统]][[希蒙·佩雷斯|希蒙·佩雷斯]]称奥巴马的就职是美国“伟大的一天”<ref name="WLACoOI">{{cite web | url = http://www.dw.de/world-leaders-adversaries-comment-on-obama-inauguration/a-3963354 | title = World Leaders, Adversaries Comment on Obama Inauguration | accessdate = 2014-10-30 | date = 2009-01-20 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141030144819/http://www.dw.de/world-leaders-adversaries-comment-on-obama-inauguration/a-3963354 | archivedate = 2014-10-30 | work = Deutsche Welle }}</ref>，[[英国首相|英国首相]][[戈登·布朗|戈登·布朗]]也表示，“全世界都在见证奥巴马总统就职，见证美国历史和世界历史都进入新的篇章”<ref>{{cite news | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141012073257/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/obama_inauguration/7840565.stm | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/obama_inauguration/7840565.stm | title = In quotes:Leaders welcome Obama | date = 2009-01-20 | accessdate = 2014-10-30 | publisher = BBC News | archivedate = 2014-10-12 }}</ref>。

部分国家领导人对奥巴马就职反应较为冷淡，甚至有些地区完全没有进行报道。[[古巴共产党|古巴共产党]]第一书记[[菲德尔·卡斯特罗|菲德尔·卡斯特罗]]的弟弟[[古巴国务委员会主席|古巴国务委员会主席]][[劳尔·卡斯特罗|劳尔·卡斯特罗]]称奥巴马“看起来像是个好人，我希望他好运”<ref name="cubacongrats">{{cite news | url = http://www.topnews.in/raul-castro-calls-obama-good-man-wishes-him-luck-2113300 | title = Raul Castro calls Obama "a good man", wishes him luck | date = 2009-01-21 | publisher = ''TopNews Magazine'' (India) | accessdate = 2014-10-30 | archive-date = 2011-05-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110525111801/http://www.topnews.in/raul-castro-calls-obama-good-man-wishes-him-luck-2113300 | dead-url = no }}</ref>，古巴[[全国人民政权代表大会|全国人民政权代表大会]]主席[[里卡多·阿拉尔孔|里卡多·阿拉尔孔]]则在评价奥巴马时称，“即将上任的（美国）总统是个很大的问号”<ref name="cubacongrats" />。[[伊朗|伊朗]]外交部长[[马努切赫尔·穆塔基|马努切赫尔·穆塔基]]（{{lang|en|Manouchehr Mottaki}}）表示希望两国关系走上新的发展方向，他指出：“如果奥巴马能选择正确的道路，弥补过去（的失误），收敛美国的敌意和霸权，并修正以前政治上的错误，（那么）我们也不会有任何敌意”<ref name="WLACoOI" />。[[俄罗斯|俄罗斯]]国有的[[第一频道_(俄罗斯)|第一频道]]是该国最大规模的[[电视频道|电视频道]]，该台的傍晚时段主打新疗节目中以很小的篇幅报道了奥巴马的就职典礼，将这一天的大部分时间用于报道该国与[[乌克兰|乌克兰]]之间的[[天然气|天然气]]冲突<ref name="WwOi">{{cite news | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141030151746/http://variety.com/2009/scene/news/world-watches-obama-inauguration-1117998807/ | url = http://variety.com/2009/scene/news/world-watches-obama-inauguration-1117998807/ | title = World watches Obama inauguration: International audiences have mixed views | accessdate = 2014-10-30 | date = 2009-01-20 | work = Variety | author = Thomas, Archie | archivedate = 2014-10-30 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。[[中华人民共和国|中华人民共和国]]国营的[[中国中央电视台|中国中央电视台]]直播了奥巴马的就职典礼，并[[同声传译|同声传译]]成[[现代标准汉语|普通话]]，时间上略有延迟，以便对具体内容进行[[中华人民共和国言论审查|审查]]。当奥巴马说到“先辈们面对[[法西斯主义|法西斯主义]]和[[共产主义|共产主义]]”时，电视台突然将讲话的画面切换成演播室的评论<ref name="bbcbristow">{{cite news | last = Bristow | first = Michael | title = Obama speech censored in China | publisher = BBC News | date = 2009-01-21 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140904002016/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/7841580.stm | archivedate = 2014-09-04 | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/7841580.stm | accessdate = 2014-10-30 }}</ref><ref name="scranton">{{cite news | work = The Huffington Post | accessdate = 2009-03-02 | last = Chang | first = Anita | date = 2009-01-21 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131109151646/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/01/21/china-censors-parts-of-ob_n_159603.html | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/01/21/china-censors-parts-of-ob_n_159603.html | title = China Censors Parts of Obama's Speech | archivedate = 2013-11-09 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。[[朝鲜民主主义人民共和国|朝鲜民主主义人民共和国]]国营的平面、广播和电视媒体完全没有报道奥巴马的就职典礼，而是报道有关[[赤道几内亚|赤道几内亚]]迎接朝鲜大使的新闻<ref name="bbcworld">{{cite news | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/obama_inauguration/7839486.stm | title = World hopes on Obama | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141026100132/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/obama_inauguration/7839486.stm | date = 2009-01-21 | publisher = BBC News | accessdate = 2014-10-30 | archivedate = 2014-10-26 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。

[[伊拉克|伊拉克]]普通市民对美国新总统就职持谨慎乐观态度。一位伊拉克市民指出：“如果（奥巴马）做的能有他说得那么好，那我们所有的问题都将迎刃而解”，他还补充道，“（奥巴马）是个好人，但伊拉克很多人都相信美国总统都是一副德性，我们（国家只）是他们利益的游乐场”<ref name="iraqview">{{cite news | url = http://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/jan/20/obama-inauguration-global-reaction | title = Jubilation and resignation as world reacts to arrival of new US president | last = Dehghan | first = Saeed Kamali | author2 = Rice, Xan | author3 = Harding, Luke | author4 = Chulov, Martin | author5 = Carroll, Rory and McCarthy, Rory | date = 2009-01-21 | work = [[卫报|The Guardian]] | location = United Kingdom | accessdate = 2014-10-30 | archive-date = 2020-07-31 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200731144436/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/jan/20/obama-inauguration-global-reaction | dead-url = no }}</ref>。另一位市民则相信“奥巴马不会像之前一样……但他也没有太多时间来向我们证明自己”<ref name="iraqview" />。

